name: StarEvents, Inc
html_setlist:
Adding to the quality of life for local residentsProviding an opportunity for the general public to unite and celebrate
Driving local, regional, and national tourismDeveloping a vehicle to showcase a communities strengths and highlight the fabric of the neighborhood
Showcasing a positive community brand and image to the media, business community, residents, and visitorsIncreasing awareness that offers a positive message to be shared with all
Creating a positive economic impact that translates into jobs, tax revenues, and enhanced infrastructure improvements for the local communityEnhancing local businesses with an increase in foot-traffic that drives revenue
Providing enhanced exposure opportunities for the arts, not-for-profit causes, and many other community programs and venuesCreating a vehicle for artisans, local businesses, and community groups to showcase their productsand services
Promoting volunteerism and bonding the many elements of the community togetherGiving residents a way to give back to their community
Encouraging community investment, participation, creativity, and visionShowcasing a footprint to express the arts
Building irreplaceable ‘community capital’ for the futureBuilding communities for a better tomorrow!
html_data:
StarEvents is Chicago’s award-winning event company that specializes in producing world-class community celebrations and festivals. We have spent the past 16 years dedicated to raising money and awareness for community groups and local, nonprofit organizations.

Our Chicago festivals are specifically designed to enhance the vitality of the communities in which they are held. They produce an incredible amount of positive economic impact for the surrounding areas and generate an enormous amount of visibility that enhances local business.

Special events are one of the few opportunities that allow people to get together and celebrate. In this face-paced world, special events provides human contact that is vital to a well-balanced community. Festivals are also an ideal footprint that provides an amazing array of artistic outlets in a way that is unlike any other. Artisans can showcase their wares and sell their artwork to an abundance of attendees at our Chicago events.

Businesses have an ideal opportunity to shake the hands and build relationships with potential customers at each of our Festivals. Musicians get an opportunity to take center stage and share their music with the masses at our street festivals. A well run special event is a creative outlet that truly creates a win-win for all involved!

Founded in 1996, StarEvents is one of the largest Chicago festival and event-production companies in the Midwest. We offer a wide range of creative services that include event production, event management, logistical support, public relations, marketing, and conceptual processes for all types of special events. Building communities for a better tomorrow is our primary objective.

Since our inception, StarEvents has helped raise over $5,000,000 for various charities and not-for-profit groups in and around Chicago. Our Chicago Events allocate a large portion of the proceeds to go directly into the beautification and improvement of local neighborhoods. StarEvents is dedicated to improving the quality of life in each of the communities represented in our calendar of events.
short_desc: StarEvents is Chicago's leading resource for all things related to event planning. Let us help you save time and money while ensuring your event is a huge success.

name: Curbside
html_data:
Curbside got it's start at Bradley University in Peoria Illinois back in late 2004. It wasn't until lead vocalist, Jim Herbert's senior year did they first play together on the porches of Duryea street. Soon after, they found a home in the local music scene playing both on campus and at the bars in downtown Peoria.

While remaining an acoustic trio featuring a cello, they still managed to fill a stage and find a loyal following before they all graduated and migrated north to Chicago.

They traded the backyards of Peoria for the bar stools of Chicago and in doing so, found a new home. Since then, they've recorded their first full length album titled "Somewhere to Nowhere" (available on our STORE and Itunes), and their highly anticipated follow up album entitled "Some Days". They've stayed true to their acoustic roots, but always looked for new ways to incorporate fuller sounds while introducing new instruments and sounds.

At the end of the day, Curbside is made up of five friends who just enjoy making music. They've always considered themselves lucky to have found a sound that works, but even more so... to have an audience to play to.
short_desc: Curbside got it's start at Bradley University in Peoria Illinois back in late 2004. It wasn't until lead vocalist, Jim Herbert's senior year did they first play together on the porches of Duryea street. Soon after, they found a home in the local music scene playing both on campus and at the bars in downtown Peoria.

name: Caricatures by Chuck
html_setlist: Art studio for caricature, cartoons and humorous Illustration. Caricature art from photos, live appointments and special events. Working in a variety of mediums including, pen and ink, watercolor, acrylics and oils.
html_data:
With a speciality in the field of caricature, I have over 21 years of experience, after a start at Six Flags Great America in 1985 and most recently at Navy Pier in Chicago.

My past venues have included The Excalibur Hotel in Las Vegas, The State Fair of Texas, the Hyatt Regency Resort Kauai as well as many other festival, corporate events, and trade shows around the world. My work has been published in advertisements, Magazines, Newspapers, Novelty Products, and on websites.
short_desc: With a speciality in the field of caricature, I have over 21 years of experience.

Gus Giordano Dance School has been entertaining thousands since 1953. Amy Giordano, Director, will work with you to plan the best show in dance entertainment.

We provide dancers for any event - tell us what you need and we will create the perfect dance, from swing to hip hop and everything in between.

name: Big Cat DJ
html_data:
A Deejay and VJ is often the glue for most events and it takes an experienced taste maker to read the room, smile, take requests, fill the dance floor and/or play a quiet set up front.

Big Cat DJ/VJ delivers a level of production including lighting, sound and a ‘look’ that will elevate your corporate or social event. We create an atmosphere and vibe to remember.

Big Cat DJ/VJ is also able to deliver a full video package with still pictures flown in from the photographer, branded video assets for awards shows and special events as well as logos and messaging.

html_data:
Since 1996 Rhapsody has been delivering high-powered performances for special events that pack dance floors and leave people wanting more.

Those who have had the pleasure to see the band live thrive off of their energy and are amazed at how the group seamlessly weaves from one song to another at a pace that leaves one breathless.

Allow Rhapsody to share your vision. Become part of a long history of satisfied clients and have Rhapsody Orchestra at your next event!

Rhapsody Orchestra will guarantee a sensational event and a lifetime of wonderful memories while ensuring ease and comfort in the planning process.

How is Rhapsody Orchestra unique?

Rhapsody Orchestra has the talent and experience to customize music for events. While having a large selection of Swing, Motown, Classic Rock and Disco, the band is continually staying current by adding new songs to their repertoire.Rhapsody Orchestra has the ability to accommodate various budgets, venues and parties by having flexible band sizes.Rhapsody Orchestra provides personal service for every event. It's important to understand and respect clients' tastes. Planning an event is no small task and our prompt communication is crucial to every question you have.
short_desc: Rhapsody Orchestra offers the best in quality live music entertainment for special occasions including weddings, corporate events, trade shows, charity benefits and festivals.

name: Chris Sarlas Orchestra
html_data:
Sarlas Music, Inc. doesn't hide behind marketing gimmicks and tactics aimed at distracting the consumer. Our Chicago wedding bands focus on music of the highest quality and getting your guests out on the dance floor to have a fabulous time.

From timeless standards made popular by Frank Sinatra, songs refreshed for the 21st Century by Michael Buble, through contemporary hits of Bruno Mars, Rihanna, Kelly Clarkson, Katy Perry, David Guetta, Adele, Jessie J, Pitbull, and Lady Gaga, we take ALL music seriously so we can get everyone dancing!

name: Typhanie Monique
html_data:
Typhanie Monique has achieved international status as a rising star vocalist by immersing herself in her true passion.

Versed in a wide range of genres and influences including jazz, funk, hip-hop, pop and improvised freestyle, the soulful-voiced chanteuse, bandleader and songwriter has earned a reputation as a fearless boundary-crosser and a natural born frontwoman with superb scatting chops and well-honed emcee skills.
short_desc: Typhanie Monique has achieved international status as a rising star vocalist by immersing herself in her true passion.

name: Scott Burns
html_data:
Possessing a warm, expressive sound, an energetic rhythmic feel, and formidable melodic and harmonic insight, saxophonist Scott Burns has been a fixture on the Chicago jazz scene since moving to the city in 1998.  A native of Dayton, Ohio, Scott began his education and professional career in jazz in nearby Cincinnati.  After graduating at the top of his class from the University of Cincinnati College-Conservatory of Music, Scott became an in-demand player in the greater Cincinnati/Dayton area. 

Performance credits include regular appearances as both leader and sideman at the landmark Blue Wisp Jazz Club, performances with powerhouse drummer John von Ohlen & the Blue Wisp Big Band, the PsychoAcoustic Orchestra, and the Cincinnati Pops Orchestra.  He also performed in concert alongside legendary jazz trumpeter Clark Terry as part of a Cincinnati jazz series.
short_desc: Possessing a warm, expressive sound, an energetic rhythmic feel, and formidable melodic and harmonic insight, saxophonist Scott Burns has been a fixture on the Chicago jazz scene since moving to the city in 1998.

Chicago-based dec8de (pronounced: decade) pays homage to the first wave of Alternative bands from the early 80’s through early 90’s.

name: Dayna Malow
html_data:
Dayna Malow has spent her professional career making her own music and that of others, come to life. Her personal style spans many musical genres, and her songwriting knows no boundaries.

Because of this, on any given night you may hear her singing at a small corner café or coffee shop, at a smoky jazz club, on stage at a crowded neighborhood bar, playing for a large crowd at a regional music festival, or under the bright lights at a regal theater or performance center.

name: A JERSEY VOICE: Sinatra to Springsteen...and Everyone in Between
html_data:
A former cast member of Chicago's long running hit, JERSEY BOYS, I have two offerings available for events.  These two offerings can be booked on 2 different nights or combined together for a longer show:

The first is my solo concert, A JERSEY VOICE: Sinatra to Springsteen...and Everyone in Between.  Featuring song selections from the 1940's through today, the concert includes songs made popular by such artists as Frank Sinatra, Dean Martin, Billy Joel, Bruce Springsteen and of course, Frankie Valli and the Four Seasons.  Along with a hot seven piece band (many of them "JB" alum) audiences are sure to love this great evening of entertainment!

The second offering is A JERSEY BOYS Tribute Show; A 45 minute show that I perform with the TVK Orchestra, one of Chicago's busiest and most well respected corporate, special event and wedding dance bands.  The Tribute features all of the Four Season's most well known hits, including "Sherry", "Big Girls Don't Cry", "Walk LIke A Man", "Dawn", "Workin' My Way Back To You", "Oh What a Night" and many more.  The show can also be followed by dance music to get the festival crowd on their feet for however long you'd like.

The TVK Orchestra is one of Chicago's premier wedding, corporate and special event bands who's members perform, record and tour with world-renowned artists and grace the stages of the CSO, Lyric Opera and varied music clubs in Chicago.  They are also the only band in the Chicago area offering this type of tribute and the only band that has permanent members in its line up who performed in the Chicago company of JERSEY BOYS during its entire 3 year run.  This brings an authenticity and credibility to the material from the show that is unmatched by any band anywhere!

html_data:
In the costume and character of Ben Franklin, I present motivational, even inspirational talks to groups of all kinds, large and small.

I bring over 40 yrs of teaching and 50 yrs of theatrical experience to making history come alive for modern audiences. Ben is an unexpected but always welcome speaker; wise, witty, and fun. Because Ben invented the concept of the professional association and contributed to his community and nation in so many, different ways,

Ben is an appropriate speaker for an enormous variety of events. I tailor my presentations to the needs and focus of each client.
short_desc: In the costume and character of Ben Franklin, I present motivational, even inspirational talks to groups of all kinds, large and small.

We are not your typical band. If you are seeking a truly great group to represent you and your organization, I hope you will give us a look.

Featuring great music, a fantastic stage show and great vocals, the band has performed throughout the US and Europe. We are a very professional group of musicians and entertainers, who would like to seek new opportunities. 

Testimonials:

Oh my Gosh Wes...I have heard so many positive comments from people about the band that night. I received 3 phone calls during the party telling me how wonderful everything was. So many nice compliments ! Jules also told me that you agreed to play at our picnic at the end of June. I was so happy to hear that. You have no idea how much I wanted to be at the party. Thanks for all your efforts in working with us at the club. I'm sure that the word of how fun it was that night is being passed around. Word gets spread to other clubs very fast. Thanks for everything Wes If you are searching for a multi talented country band that will add entertainment and fun to your party, then look no further! Ernie Givens and The White Lies Band will meet and surpass any expectations you could possibly have for a country band. If fact, if these country boys can’t set your toes a tapping then your foot must be asleep. We have had all kinds of bands play at our club but this band performs on a much higher level. The perfect mix of fun and professionalism. Ernie Givens and The White Lies Band are the definition of country gentlemen Craig F. Bonifas Phoenix Club President Aurora, Ill. Hi Wes - Just wanted to get in touch with you (and all the guys) to extend our most humble thanks to all of you for the fantastic evening we had when you were here recently. Everyone down here at the campground absolutely raved about the band. And around here, word spreads fast and I know everyone will remember "Ernie Givens and the White Lies Band" for a long, long time! You're definitely the best entertainment this campground has ever had! We're all looking forward to seeing you here again next year. html_data: Wild Daisy is THE most energetic, dynamic female-fronted country band in the Chicagoland area. The band plays current, upbeat country, with a few pop/rock songs thrown in. Wild Daisy established a reputation in Chicago for consistently delivering high-quality, family-friendly, crowd-interactive, entertaining shows, with musicianship and energy that cannot be matched.(See below for praise for Wild Daisy from former clients.) Wild Daisy’s past gigs include: First Midwest Bank Amphitheatre VIP Pavilion (Pre and Post Brad Paisley concert), U.S. Cellular Field (home of the Chicago White Sox), Schaumburg Septemberfest MAIN stage (opening for country icon Mark Chesnutt), Toby Keith’s Bar and Grill Chicago, The Saloon at Bourbon Street, Chicago’s Willis Tower, Old Crow Smokehouse Wrigleyville, Oak Lawn’s Fall on the Green, Cadillac Ranch, Firewater Saloon and more. name: Sam Fazio
html_data:
Sam Fazio's music is hip, elegant and bold. He puts a wonderful new spin on the songs we love. Whether he’s singing a swing standard or pop classic, his soulful yet classic style comes shining through. Sam’s style is reminiscent of classic singers like Frank Sinatra and Bobby Darin, yet current like the sounds of Michael Buble.

name: South Boulevard Band
html_setlist: Midnight Hour Here I Am Shakey Ground Cross Cut Saw Ordinary Man Love and Happiness Steppin’ In/Steppin’ Out 99-1/2 Happy Havin’ Fun Man’s World Leave Your Hat On Born Under a Bad Sign Grits Ain’t Groceries Band Intro/Too Funky in Here Take Me to the River
html_data:
A rockin' R & B/Blues/Soul group with a high-energy, harp-playing front man, a "tight as rope" rhythm section and an amazing horn section, the crowd-pleasing South Boulevard Band gets its fans--from 17 to 70!--up and dancing every time.

South Boulevard is a new band consisting of veterans of the Chicago music scene. The members, with almost 200 years of cumulative musical experience, have shared the stage with such notables as Muddy Waters, James Cotton, Sonny Terry, Brownee Mcghee and Hubert Sumlin.

They have recorded at CBS Records Chicago, Capitol records LA, Cherokee Sound LA, United Artists Studio LA, Electric Ladyland NY and Blue Wave, Vancouver, BC.

Rhythm section Steve Flugum (bass) and Steve Capillo (drums) provide a tight, funky bottom that has evolved over 40 years (that’s right—40!) of playing together.

Guitarists Willie Shields and Chris Discher lock in tough, tight rhythms and heartfelt solos. While having two distinct playing styles, their singing guitars make you feel every note.

This core group is joined by the Third Coast Horn section, two more talented musicians (and their baritone and tenor saxophones.) Chicago natives Bob Fried and Miles Tesar bring with them years of formal education; Miles has a Bachelor’s degree in Saxophone and Bob is a Master of composition who has worked toward his Doctorate in Ethnomusicology. Their skills have also brought these professionals all over the world. From Australia to St. Lucia, they’ve played Broadway musicals, chorale pieces, television scores, theatrical productions, gigs with Charo (coochie coochie!)—oh, and of course, rock, jazz and blues. Bob and Miles’ amazing accents and clever contratempos raise that special South Boulevard sound to a whole new dimension.
Tying all this music together are the raspy, deep, soulful vocals of Mr. Dudley Fair. This lead singer’s raw emotion commands the audience and brings them to their feet. His explosive harp playing is reminiscent of such luminaries as Little Walter and James Cotton.South Boulevard delivers a great show every time they take the stage.
short_desc: South Boulevard is a new band consisting of veterans of the Chicago music scene.

html_data:
NORTHSIDE has been rocking the Chicagoland circuit for over a decade.

Northside is a 5 member Rock n Roll tribute band based out of Chicago, covering music from the 1970's through present day. Northside honors bands ranging from classic rock's Led Zeppelin and The Rolling Stones, as well as modern and alternative rock greats such as Nirvana, No Doubt and U2 as well as a montage of dance songs ranging from the 70's to present day.

In 2003, drummer Chris Stamos, bassist Bob Spilios and guitarist Louie Kritikos reunited their band. They now have been playing together for over two decades. They recruited singer and keyboardist Rebecca Bolluyt and Northside Band was born. George Skoubis reunited with the band contributing with some guitar, keyboards and back-up vocals completing Northside’s current line-up and sound.

Four of the 5 members were born and grew up together on the Northside of Chicago. It is evident by watching them perform live, that Northside is just 5 great friends having a blast performing music together. This attitude and kinship is always sensed by the audiences and has a way of creating a “good times for all” mood for anyone at the show.

Northside has gig’d at such Chicagoland venues as The Cubby Bear in Wrigleyville, Captian Morgans Club at Wrigley Field, The Beat Kitchen, 27 Live in Evanston, Blarney Island on The Fox River & Abbey Pub in Chicago as well as The Summer on Southport fest, Taste of Lincoln Ave fest., Taste of Lakeview fest, Andersonville Midsumma Fest, Retro on Roscoe, Edison Park Fest and was the head liner at the Ignite Fest '11 & '12. .
short_desc: One of Chicagoland's BEST Cover bands!

html_data:
We are an eight piece Rolling Stones Tribute based in Chicago.

The Rolling Clones were born on the corner of Armitage and Halstead at Nick’s in the early 1990′s. A well-known financial analyst used to frequent Nick’s on Friday afternoons after battling the financial markets all week. This analyst would come into Nick’s looking for a few pints, a few laughs, and lots of Rolling Stones songs on the jukebox. The problem was that this particular analyst faced a major nemesis in the bartender who had very little tolerance for Rolling Stones songs on the jukebox. This Friday afternoon drama is captured brilliantly in the video Start Me Up.
short_desc: An 8 piece band dedicated to the music of the Rolling Stones. Need we say more?

html_data:
Comfortably Floyd is a Pink Floyd Tribute show that performs Pink Floyd music authentic to the original artists along with a multimedia video projection and multicolored lasers to create a true Pink Floyd experience. Comfortably Floyd is suitable as an experienced headliner with lasers, multimedia, and up to 3 hours of performance, or as an opening act playing just the most well-known Pink Floyd hits, such as "Money" and "Another Brick in the Wall", with as quick as a 25-30 minute setup time.

Here's what separates this act from many other local acts: Comfortably Floyd's social media presence is very strong and growing at a faster pace than any other band in the area with about 4,000 Facebook fans and over 25,000 video views/hits on YouTube since 2013.

Show promoters are helped out tremendously by the amount of social media and public access available for people to see the high quality of our show that will motivate people to attend. Very rarely, if ever, do any of the top local cover acts play music from Pink Floyd, even though Pink Floyd has sold over 200 million albums. Only The Beatles and Led Zeppelin have sold more rock albums, as local covers of those 2 legendary bands have recently been over-booked in this area. With a very diverse demographic reach, Pink Floyd music is tame enough for elderly audiences while still relevant and recognizable to younger audiences.

Roger Waters, with his tour of Pink Floyd's "The Wall", was the 2nd highest money-making musician of 2012 with Chicago being the only city in the world that sold out 5 shows. Tribute shows like Australian Pink Floyd and Brit Floyd are some of the world's biggest drawing cover bands because people love to see a Pink Floyd show, and that's why fans turn out to see Comfortably Floyd. The USA longs for a quality Pink Floyd show they can go to see at local festivals and at medium to large sized indoor venues.

As a headliner at a night time show (after dusk), Comfortably Floyd enhances the show with multicolored lasers and a 5000 lumen video projection for multimedia that goes together with the live music. This creates the full Pink Floyd experience that millions long to enjoy. Even with experience and fan appeal as a headliner and also as an opener for major national acts, Comfortably Floyd is a band that will give event planners the most for their money with performances that will be memorable for years to come.
short_desc: Comfortably Floyd is a Pink Floyd Tribute band show that performs Pink Floyd music with a multimedia video projection and multicolored lasers to create a true Pink Floyd experience.
categories: Pink Floyd Tribute Show, Tribute Band, Cover Band, Classic Rock

Crafting catchy folk/pop melodies with meaningful lyrics, Sean Magwire has forged a unique brand of songwriting. A native of Angola, Indiana, Sean grew up listening to the classics on an old tape deck before learning guitar at age 15. name: Jon Conover
html_data:
Jon Conover is a Chicagoland singer/songwriter/recording artist that has recorded two albums and toured extensively nationally and internationally. His latest album, Make it Til November, was recorded in Los Angeles, CA, and features performances by industry giants Kenny Aronoff on drums, Ed Roth on keys, Linda Taylor on guitar and Andrew Ford on Bass.

Jon has recently returned from an extensive tour of Ireland that earned him media coverage and regular plays on Ireland’s biggest radio stations featuring his singles, How God Chooses and I’m Coming Home. Jon has played to sold-out crowds in Ireland, California and across the Midwest, touring mostly with his producer, Ed Roth. Ed has recording credits with names like the Avett Brothers, Will Smith, Coolio, Chad Smith’s Bombastic Meatbats, R&B vocalist Mya and Grammy nominee Sophie B. Hawkins.

Conover has already enjoyed international success and has shared the stage with some of the biggest names in the industry, and he has no signs of slowing down. Below is the band Line-up that backed Jon Conover on his latest CD "Make It til November." Drums: Kenny Aronoff (John Cougar Mellencamp, Smashing Pumpkins) Bass: Andrew Ford (Whitney Houston, Al Jarreau) Guitar: Linda Taylor (Tracy Chapman, Who's line Is It Anyways Show Band) Keys: Ed Roth (Coolio, Sophie B. Hawkins, Peter Frampton...)

Jin & Tonic Band (JTB) Jin & Tonic Band is one of the premier country bands in the mid-west and has played many of the larger venues in the Chicagoland area, including Joe's on Weed St, House of Blues, The Cubby Bear, Arlington Park Racetrack, River's and Blue Chip Casino. JTB has shared the stage with some of the biggest names in country music today, including Lady Antebellum and The Band Perry.

Jin & Tonic was formed by Jenn Fletcher ("Jin" - the misspelling is intentional!) and Toni LaManna-Siprut ("Tonic") in 2005. This seven piece band hosts two female lead singers, two male singers, a fiddle player that will leave you speechless, a pounding rhythm section, and two amazing guitarists featuring their banjo and mandolin skills along the way.

Every Country Song tells a Story, and Jin and Tonic Band does just that, with a show that’s One Big Party. Covering the best country music out there and a few surprises along the way. Known for their incredible harmonies and memorizing stage presence, it is a show you won't forget.

Jin & Tonic Acoustic (JTA) Don't have a large enough stage for a 7-piece band? This version of JTB can be scaled to include percussion and bass if the room and budget permits. Jin & Tonic Acoustic delivers a lower key version of the Jin & Tonic Band perfect for smaller rooms or mid-week shows.

Jin & Tonic Band and Jin & Tonic Acoustic can be booked locally and nationally for club & bar gigs, festivals, and private events, including corporate events.
short_desc: A fun and popular Chicago country band playing great music for good times!!

html_data: Meet the Beetles is a loving tribute to John, Paul, George, and Ringo.  Each band member is a skilled musician as well as a talented actor/impersonator, paying homage to his character.  Performing the early Beatle hits (such as "I Want To Hold Your Hand" and "Help!"),  the band recreates the look, sound, and incredible energy of a live Beatles concert.  With the later songs (such as "Revolution" and "Something"), the performance whisks the audience into the psychedelia of the late sixties. The illusion is complete with costumes, accents, vintage equipment (just like the Beatles used), and witty banter.  It's not scripted, so every show is unique. Meet The Beetles high energy show has been featured at venues including the Navy Pier Grand Ballroom, US Cellular Field, Conseco Fieldhouse, Pepsi Colliseum, and the Mall Of America.
short_desc: Meet the Beetles is a loving tribute to John, Paul, George, and Ringo.

Please see our website for a current list of the songs we play.  We have a broad range of music and will work closely with you to create a play-list and musical entertainment package tailored specifically to your needs and to the event.

In addition to our traditional dance music, we can also provide a live instrumental Jazz set during a cocktail hour or dinner, upon request. 

http://www.thehatguys.com/booking.html
html_data:
The Hat Guys is one of the premiere wedding, corporate party and special events bands in Chicago. For nearly a decade, dozens of well-known and highly-respected charities, corporations and civic organizations have trusted The Hat Guys to deliver top-tier musical entertainment at their most important events. Similarly, we have been a part of some extraordinarily joyous and beautiful moments with newlyweds and their families and friends. All of our clients have chosen us because we play a wide variety of music from the past five decades, all of which has one thing in common: it fills the dance floor from the first note to the last. Over the years, we have performed extensively at dozens of weddings, and for dozens of corporate, civic and charitable clients, at many of Chicago's premier venues, including the House of Blues, the Park West, Union Station, the River East Arts Center, The Hard Rock Cafe, Navy Pier's Grand Ballroom, and the Chicago History Museum. Our clients have included MetLife, BP, Chicago Cares, the USO of Illinois, Wells Fargo Capital Finance, the ATI Foundation, Rush-Copley Medical Center, WGN Children's Charities, Crayola, Y-Me, Bright Pink, Advocate Christ Hospital, and the Illinois Restaurant Association. Please see our website for more details about our experience and contact us at info@thehatguys.com with any questions.

Full service cover band.

html_data:
Everyone has a voice. A style. A unique and perfect mix of elements that makes the world stop and take notice. From Chicago to Cabo...Hawaii to the BVI, Green Thirteen has been called on to hear those voices, amplify them and fuel the party of a lifetime...time and time again. Building the perfect set for every audience and delivering a professional high energy show has become Green Thirteen's signature and the new quality benchmark for live musical entertainment in Chicago, across the country and around the world.

ENERGIZE: Green Thirteen's song list contains a seemingly endless group of the most popular music ever released. What if you could hit "shuffle" on your favorite playlist and have the music come to life right before your eyes. That's what happens at every single Green Thirteen performance. A Green Thirteen show is a live, seamless, exciting mix of only the best songs from the most popular artists in every era of modern music.

Green Thirteen performs over a hundred shows every year and uses its experience to stay in touch with every turn and trend in today's popular music scene. Many of Green Thirteen's performances are documented in the newly developed "Flash Rewind" video series. These videos encapsulate the energy, excitement and consistency that their audiences have come to expect. Beyond the music, they truly care about every concert and event they play and work just as hard off the stage as on it to guarantee an unforgettable experience every time they step up to the microphone. How can Green Thirteen be so sure they can nail the thrills, excitement and energy of a free fall through the best live soundtrack ever created? Because it's not about us...it's all about you...

CLIENT QUOTES:

Amazing!! Green Thirteen was the band at my reception and they truly made my wedding unforgettable. Leading up to the wedding, they were very helpful with the planning - very relaxed yet very organized with awesome planning guides that explained everything. They were super friendly and accommodating throughout the whole process. As far as the reception...THEY ROCKED!! The music was amazing--several guests commented that they felt like they had gone to see an actual band play at a venue! They said, "I would buy tickets to see this band!!" The band was also super kid-friendly, allowing some of the younger guests come up and help them "play". Months after the wedding, I'm still getting compliments on Green Thirteen. -SARAHDEBJ, 8/13/2011, Review on WeddingChannel.com Green Thirteen - The Perfect Wedding Band. The band will make or break your reception so, if you want a crowd-pleasing, "dance all night" band, choose Green Thirteen. They're talented beyond words, fun to work with, professional, and not to mention...affordable!!!! Absolutely everyone loved them. As Mother-of-the-Bride, Patrick instantly appealed to me. "You seem like one of us" I kept telling him. My daughter agreed and said Green Thirteen was everything she hoped for and more. We would gladly hire them again! -MRSGREEN 444, 6/17/2011, Review on "the Knot" Hello. My wife Allie and I got married at the Blue Heron this summer on June 25. Thanks for everything. You guys were great! Allie and I wanted to tell you that we've been to a few other weddings this summer and it made us realize how much you guys kicked a$$! We will always recommend you to our friends. Take care. -Richard & Allie Whiteman, 6/24/11, Wedding Reception, Blue Heron Banquets IN Our heartfelt thanks go out to you for making Darcy & Tyler's wedding one that will be long remembered by many. Your talents and exuberance radiated throughout the night. As parents, we truly appreciate all you did to add to the night's success. As artists, you guys rock and are, all in all, pretty awesome! -Ken & Cindy Pavlik, 9/24/11, Wedding Reception, Willowbrook Ballroom IL If we were planning another wedding tomorrow, I'd use you guys again in a heartbeat. You were great! -Nancy Hirsh, 9/18/11, Wedding Reception, Chicago History Museum, IL Green Thirteen was simply incredible. Very few live acts have the energy they have. From the beginning to the end they were the glue that kept our party together. They are THE premier party band in Chicago and provide a great sound and a great time! Thank you...you guys are simply the best! -Emily Ferguson., 9/10/11, Wedding Reception, NIU Campus Naperville When the dance floor is never empty & the house lights come on and nobody wants to leave, you know you had a blast of a band. Green Thirteen provided professional coordination of our event, included the children at our wedding by allowing them to play drums & guitar and kept everyone on the dance floor all night. Camille even made some of our family look good by joining them on the dance floor. We danced more than we have in years. -Hugh & Carolyn, 9/4/11, Wedding Reception, East Bank Club Chicago Green Thirteen promised and over delivered. they were highly professional musicians, organized, flexible, helpful and most importantly personable. Although talent is essential, being able to channel it to meet a variety of musical tastes and make it fun is a difficult task. We couldn't have asked for more...it was a wonderful evening. Eric & Randy Hartwig, 9/3/11, Wedding Reception, Wausau WI THANK YOU!!!! I was blown away by how many people were on the dance floor from the first song. Today is my first day back at work and everyone has told me what a wonderful time they had and even mentioned how versatile the band was. Everyone really enjoyed your music. You guys did a FANTASTIC job! From the bottom of my heart THANK YOU!!!! -Kristen S, 10/16/10, Wedding Reception, OakBrook, IL We hired Green Thirteen for our wedding reception and were absolutely blown away! The performers were very accommodating, handling all of the introductions, and timing for speeches so that I could just sit back and relax. When they started playing live, people crowded the dance floor and didn't leave until the very end of the reception. I had people dancing who I'd never seen on the dance floor before! All in all the music was amazing, I would recommend this band to everyone. It was by far the best wedding I've ever been to, and I owe it to Green Thirteen! -Chrissie G, 1/9/2010, Wedding Reception, Des Plaines, IL Everyone had a great time - nothing but compliments! Their set up looked fantastic and they really made the reception something we will remember for a long time. I even asked Rob to try to make up a new version of our first dance song so it would sound more modern. After hearing it, I think they should record it...it was incredible! Rob even gave us some insight on the hot spots in Mexico for our honeymoon. Music & Travel Planning! Thanks for everything, Rob! I'll report back on the Don Julio 1942 when we get back! -Jackie K, 10/18/2009, Wedding Reception, Streamwood, IL We would like to thank Green Thirteen for playing at our wedding reception and thank Gigmasters for helping us find them! The entire reception was amazing beyond our highest expectations. The dance floor was filled the whole night - even by family members I've never seen leave their seat at a wedding! All we heard the entire night was that we found the best band anyone's ever heard at a wedding. Rob was patient with us and helped us through the whole planning process. He even had the band customize an entire medley for the first dances and it was like something you'd see in a movie. Awesome! Everything flowed together perfectly and extremely professionally. -Erick H, 8/15/2009, Wedding Reception, Glencoe, IL We do this event every year and they raised the bar on what we should expect in a band. They were very helpful with announcements and speeches throughout and their live performance was out of this world. Somehow they went from old to new material all night without ever stopping between songs. Everyone loved them and they wore us out from dancing! -Sarah D, 10/3/2009, Corporate Function, Burlington, WI This band was fantastic. They played for 4 hours with one 15 min. break and never stopped between songs. They were completely professional. There price was reasonably set. If any thing I would think they could ask more. We all had a great night. -Thatcher W, 10/10/2009, Birthday Party (Adults), Wilmette, IL Our company picnic was for 500 people. Everyone enjoyed the music and the band was most helpful. We received a number of compliments about the band and would hire Green Thirteen again. Bill Kay Auto Group -Nina M, 8/10/2008, Corporate Function, Lisle, IL I really had many compliments on the band from guests, and they were very professional, and talented. I would definetly hire them again. They played a wide variety of music to accomadate my guests, and everyone appreciated them. We really had fun! Thanks to Green 13! -Christina K, 10/31/2008, Halloween Party, Berkeley, IL I hired Green Thirteen as entertainment for our high school reunion. I don't organize things like that very often and it took a lot of time and planning. I think the best thing I did was to hire Green Thirteen. As soon as I booked them it was like they lifted a weight off my shoulders. I've never had the opportunity to work with such a talented and professional group of people. I got nothing but rave compliments about them all night. They really made me look great. If you had a rating higher than 5 stars in every category I would give it to them! -John A, 8/22/2009, Reunion, Orland Park, IL Green Thirteen was absolutely brilliant! They were easy to work with and everyone loved them. They even learned a special song for our first dance that a family friend in from Ireland sang with the band. I checked in to some other well known Chicago bands for our wedding and couldn't be happier that I chose Green Thirteen. My wife is an event planner and said that she will be using them for events in the future. -Alan D, 8/27/2010, Wedding Reception, Chicago, IL Green Thirteen was great! The only person not happy was the reception hall manager because nobody wanted to leave! LOL Everything was very professional and fun and the music selection was really great. We even had a few "wedding crashers" from other receptions taking place that night who said that they wished they could stay at ours! Great job guys. I'm so glad we found you and we will see you again really soon! -Kathy P, 8/21/2010, Wedding Reception, Kildeer, IL Green Thirteen rocked! They went over all our expectations and our reception kicked a#$! They were very easy to work with and made sure that everything we wanted happened. The bridal party intros were great and they even brought in microphones and speakers for the ceremony which was in the reception hall. I didn't want a cheesy wedding. Green Thirteen was able to make everybody happy and still keep things upbeat and young feeling. I'd recommend them to anyone and we can't wait to go out and see them again soon! -Bobby C, 8/20/2010, Wedding Reception, Chicago, IL I can't thank Green Thirteen enough for playing at our wedding reception! The music was amazing - they somehow went from older songs all the way to Usher and the Black Eyed Peas and sounded amazing on everything. Everyone we talked to had a great time! They were also extremely helpful with the planing for the night and they were really professional and organized as everything unfolded. I put a lot of thought and planning into our reception and after seeing how great everything turned out, the BEST decision I made was to hire Green Thirteen! -Jodi C, 7/10/2010, Wedding Reception, Lake Geneva, WI Everybody LOVED Green Thirteen! They absolutely made our reception. I would recommend this band to anyone who wants a fun dance band that plays a mix of songs for all ages. The sound equipment sounded extremely full and clear, they were a pleasure to work with and we really feel like our wedding meant a lot to them. We feel lucky to have found a band that was easy to work with, reasonably priced and that made our wedding extra special. Thanks guys! -Paige L, 6/12/2010, Wedding Reception, Bloomington, IL Green Thirteen couldn't possibly be more professional, more talented or more fun! The reception was excellent and everyone commented on how great the band was. They were very easy to work with, handled all our requests with ease (they even somehow handled a last minute odd request by my grandmother) and made us feel at ease through the whole day with a sense that they knew exactly what they were doing. The customer service they provided and the "all-inclusive" nature of what they provided for us was well worth having them. We are absolutely thrilled that we chose Green Thirteen for our wedding - they were awesome! -Amanda M, 5/22/2010, Wedding Reception, Sauk City, WI

html_data:
Originally formed as an over-the-top tribute to the Disco music of the 70's, Libido Funk Circus has been relentlessly entertaining a wide range of audiences since it's inception in 1996. While they continue to play your favorite Disco hits, the addition of hundreds of dance & rock songs, spanning from the 60's through today, has quite literally turned LFC into a human jukebox. From the hits of the good ole' Motown days to the bass-thumping beats of today's dance music; from the always danceable Disco grooves to the new wave rock of the 80's… LFC has it "covered". Take one look at their ever-expanding song list and you will be sold!

While their legendary catalog has certainly become the band's trademark, LFC's non-stop energy, showmanship and exquisite musicality is what truly sets them apart from the rest. With top-notch, professional musicians (including both male and female lead vocalists) and hundreds of songs under its collective belt, Libido Funk Circus has all the tools to make a room move all night long!

Having performed thousands of times at clubs, weddings, corporate & private parties, sporting events, casinos and street festivals, Libido Funk Circus realizes the crucial role live entertainment plays at every type of event. With a professionalism that only comes with many years of experience, LFC is truly adept at honoring the tone you envision for your affair and can accommodate their stage apparel and musical selections to suit the evening's ambience. Capable of switching styles and genres at the drop of a hat, Libido Funk Circus can entertain any audience...from small children to the most critical musical connoisseurs!

By popular demand, Libido Funk Circus frequently performs both 70's and 80's theme nights; complete with authentic costuming and music from each era. Perfect for theme parties, class reunions and more!

If you're looking for entertainment for your next event, look no further…you've already found it. Libido Funk Circus promises to deliver a high-energy, musical tour de force to keep your event rockin' all night long!
short_desc: Libido Funk Circus has all the tools to make a room move all night long!

html_data: Born and raised in Chicago, Sashe Taylor has wields her vocal talents with unmatchable presence and taste for a wide variety of musical influences. Moving forward from her early pop records, Taylor’s recent studio work has been more focused on classic rock, blues, and jazz-related influences, a move towards music with timeless qualities. Taylor has also appeared in a theatrical production, most recently Dee Snider’s Rock & Roll Christmas Tale which ran into early 2015. Off the success of her 2014 debut EP, Dare You To Love Me, Sashe Taylor is back at work on a new full-length project that reflects her expanded tastes and a new, blues-tinged direction to her music. -Subvert Agency She is a high class woman with lots of soul. :)

name: This Must Be the Band
html_data:
“This Must Be the Band” is Chicago’s only and therefore best Talking Heads Tribute Band; they only play Talking Heads music, and, if possible, 3 to 4 hours at a time.

They formed in May 2007 on Craigslist and played the coveted pizza joint circuit, the most notable of which was the city-famous Piece Pizza in Wicker Park. Since then, they have expanded east to NYC and west to Boise, ID (yes, THAT Boise, ID). They have two main dishes on their menu: the first is a succulent “All-Request Show,” with a generous helping of audience participation, flavored slightly by improvisation. The second is the hailed “Stop Making Sense Re-Creation,” where they perform note-for-note and prop-for-prop the famous Talking Heads concert film from 1984. In 2011, they performed this show to a sold-out crowd at the Vic Theatre in Chicago.

This Must be the Band is extremely happy to play Talking Heads music night after night because the music is just that much fun. Not only has the lead singer (Charlie Otto) been called “the illegitimate son of David Byrne,” but the band boasts its very own Tina Weymouth (Jamie Jay), Bernie Worrell (Jim Dinou), Adrian Belew (covered by both Otto and Dinou), and Ednah Holt (Kasey Foster). TMBTB is available for any gathering where people need to dance: parties, weddings, bars, etc.
short_desc: “This Must Be the Band” is Chicago’s only Talking Heads Tribute Band
categories: Talking Heads Tribute, Experimental Rock, Cover Band

html_data:
As it’s been with many bands for many years, a new band forms then breaks up, re-forms, then breaks up & so on with numerous band name changes in between. Some names stick, & some, well, let’s just say, they’re better left forgotten.

Our story is not much different. We set out in the summer of 2006 to change the cover band scene & after numerous performances, periodic changes in musical direction & several personnel changes; a new direction was finally established.

Along with professional backing & a focused determination to elevate our music, our shows & provide our audiences with the very best live entertainment experience, 28 Days was formed.

Why 28 Days? We’ve heard a number of interesting reasons for the name but the reason was simple, it takes 28 Days to begin the changing of one's behavioral pattern & since we wanted to change the way our audiences viewed the “Cover Band” scene, seemed like we had a name. 28 days provides audiences with an unparalleled “Live” experience that electrifies the senses. Members consist of Kevin Triplett on Bass, Joe Maxwell on Guitar, PJ Howard on Drums & Paul Shamoun on Lead Vocals.

Since it’s official inception, 28 Days has performed hundreds of events for thousands of screaming fans. For a live entertainment experience you will NOT soon forget, check out 28 Days at a venue near you!
short_desc: Providing audiences with the very best live entertainment experience
categories: Cover Band, Wedding Band, Rock Band, Dance Band

name: Mr. Blotto
html_data:
Mr. Blotto was born in Chicago as an off-night vehicle for musicians who loved each others playing but were in different bands at the time. The only rule was that they would only play what they loved. That philosophy continues today and has led Mr. Blotto into unique musical situations.

Mr. Blotto takes the Jam band aesthetic into areas unfamiliar to the standard Jam Scene. They have been known to cover entire albums by Led Zepplin and the Who as well as perform entire shows of Country and Reggae. Artists as diverse as the Grateful Dead, the Flaming Lips, Willie Nelson and The Velvet Underground have seen their material interpreted by Mr. Blotto in the 2000+ shows the band has performed in the last 15 years, yet covers only pepper the bands hefty catalog of original material stemming from five studio albums and other unreleased crowd favorites.

Live band. Full sound system and lights available. Can play CDs and MP3s through system.
short_desc: Original and cover jam band genre including Grateful Dead, Allman Brothers, Phish, Panic, Ray Charles, Delta Blues and outlaw old school country...

html_data:
Rooted in country and laced with rock 'n roll, Chasin' Mason makes music as rugged and raw as the rough roads and wrong turns that have taken them through seven years of trial and triumph. Their miles are marked with guitars as loud as the lives they've lived and lyrics as true as their Sunday morning upbringings.

Since their formation in 2003, the Wisconsin based group has wasted little time establishing themselves as one of the hottest up and coming bands in country music. Having sold 15,000 independently released cds to their constantly growing fan base, it's evident that the band's 200 plus shows a year are bearing fruit.

A melting pot of musical influences, Chasin' Mason mixes Merle and Mellencamp with U2 and Keith Urban to create their rockin' edge with a story to tell. The guys borrow their style and passion from their diverse pasts. Pulling from musical families, hard childhoods, wrong crowds, and right girls, Chasin' Mason plays Real Life Real Lou!!!
short_desc: Chasin' Mason mixes Merle and Mellencamp with U2 and Keith Urban to create their rockin' edge with a story to tell.

name: Brothers Rage
html_data:
Brothers Rage is a quartet consisting of guitar, bass, keys, and drums. Forming in 2011, the band started creating a buzz around Chicago and Illinois by playing often at local venues and summer music festivals.

Offering a unique angle on “jamband music,” listeners took notice by repeatedly coming back to the shows time after time, resulting in a strong and loyal following. The music created leans towards the heavier side of jamband music consisting of tight, chunky riff-rock fused with jazz influenced improvisation and funky grooves. A live Brothers Rage shows consist of structured compositions balanced with free-form improvisations.

The band also covers a wide array of songs and genres ranging from Beatles to Black Sabbath; Zappa to The Police; Steely Dan to Rush; and much more!
short_desc: Tight, chunky riff-rock fused with jazz influenced improvisation and funky grooves

html_data:
The Schaumburg Illinois top forty country group Smokin Gunz was founded in the summer of 1997. Currently, the group consists of 4 full-time members, including; Jim Banke (guitar/lead vocals), David Nekola (lead guitar/vocals), Artie Specht (Bass guitar) and Robert Broz (drums/vocals), with over-whelming professionalism and dedication to the music produced by the band.

The group has traveled the Midwest performing at Clubs, Festivals and Casinos in WI, IL, IA, IN, MI and has acquired a strong fan base Smokin' Gunz musical style and background is derived from straight forward rock-n-roll, combined with hard driving, country music styles, backed by heart felt harmony vocal arrangements, with some real foot tapping dance tunes to provide musical entertainment for all types of audiences regardless of their musical preferences.

All of the group's Original material is written solely by the members themselves with inspiration based on real life experiences. Smokin' Gunz is comprised of talented musicians that become one with their instruments. Showmanship is first class and stage presence is fine tuned to a highly professional caliber not often found in the local venue circuits of the Chicagoland and surrounding areas.

Smokin' Gunz was voted number one country band in Chicago by Suburbanites Magazine and the Chicago Rocker Magazine for 2011. They are a sure bet to produce a fun and entertaining atmosphere that will be remembered for many years to come and keep the fan-base growing to unimaginable heights. Smokin Gunz has been honored by opening for some of the biggest names in country music just to name a few. Tracy Lawrence, Montgomery Gentry, Gretchen Wilson, Locash Cowboys, Dirt Drifters, Jeffery Steele, Confederate Railroad, Chris Cagle, Jake Owen and Randy Houser just to name a few.

This is definitely not your average local bar band, but, much more. In 2012 will see Smokin' Gunz back performing on the live venue circuits of the Midwest promoting their latest CD and introducing more original material and compositions that have always been the signature marks of the professionalism and dedication of a band at their musical and entertainment caliber.
short_desc: Real foot tapping dance tunes to provide musical entertainment for all types of audiences
categories: Country Band, Country Music, Chicago Country Music

name: The Flips
html_setlist: We have a new record A Harm Deep But Shining out now: http://goo.gl/r8qx6N
html_data:
Debut albums are a tough lot. Sometimes bands who've self-released a few EP's try to crank out (and, in effect, stretch out) more of the same formula that came before, somehow hoping for a different result or even recapturing the magic of their first recordings. Others aim for cookie-cutter hits, and still more experiment a bit in an attempt to stand out.
 
In the case of Chicago's The Flips, who had already generated a stellar buzz since last year with the caustic, yet harmonious Damn You & Damn Me Too EP, we get a rare journey with A Harm Deep But Shining in several directions: Vocalist/guitarist Nick Sintos and crew are just as agitated as before, with quiet/loud dynamics bursting into audio explosions, but coupled with that is the allowance of space between Sintos' seething screams and the band's crushing distortion.
 
This is evidenced right from the first track, the aptly named "Intro," as well as "Racing Stripe" and the nearly nine-minute "Bees Knees." Tempos build, cymbals shimmer with enough air to breathe, and the group  sound right at home taking the proper time needed to reach such memorable climaxes. The mostly acoustic "Let It Go" and the swaying "Cute" give some stunning spotlights to Sintos' harmonies with keyboardist Annette Nowacki, as well.
 
That's not to say the band is at all at rest. Sintos' trademark howl and Dustin Martin's guitar work are both more powerful than ever. The pummeling "God I'm Sorry" packs an emotional punch, along with "Jawbreaker" and crunch of "G-Unit," which addresses those who "play your songs for the sound of the praise." But this isn't the sound of a band with a chip on their shoulder. Their ferocious output isn't just out there to be heard, but it's the attention they get with it that then opens the listener's mind with what's actually being said.
short_desc: The Flips are a five-piece band with a distinct sound

name: Walkin' With Cash
html_setlist: Keith Furry is well aware of the complexities surrounding Johnny Cash, in fact, he embraces them. "One of my favorite lines to describe Johnny Cash is from the book 'Cash' by Rolling Stone magazine: 'Sinner, Saint, Rebel, Voice of Protest, Man of Faith', says Furry, leader of the tribute band Walkin' With Cash. Hailed as one of the most influential musicians of the 20th century, Cash had that rarest of crossover appeals, having earned induction into the Rock n Roll, Country and Gospel Halls of Fame. Furry captures those intricacies with a fan's eagerness and a musician's skill. From his note perfect trembling baritone voice to his all black outfits, every detail rings true during a Walkin' With Cash show. Of course, much of Cash's music, particularly toward the end of his stellar career, focused on moral questions and the search for redemption but Furry's rendition of this often dark and mysterious superstar never translates into a dour, over-serious experience on stage. Instead, Furry delves deep into the Cash catalog shining a spotlight on every corner of this legend-from his rockabilly beginnings to his flirty duets with wife June Carter Cash, expertly recreated in the Walkin' With Cash performances by Jan Daily. It would be hard to portray Johnny Cash and not be somewhat playful and heartwarming, "He had a wicked sense of humor" Furry says, "I'm there to have a good time and it shows". For the enthusiastic, late-blooming Furry, there's no other way to perform. Furry originally unveiled his imitation of Johnny Cash on a lark and a new passion was born. He was a percussionist and backup vocalist for a local Elvis tribute band, The Blue Suede Crew. "The lead singer needed a break to change costumes during the show and asked if I knew anyone that could sing like Johnny Cash. I surprised him by belting out "Folsom Prison Blues" and that's how I started my tribute to The Man in Black", Furry remembers. Along with Scott Wattles, as Elvis, The Blue Suede Crew became an almost instant regional draw and even recorded at the legendary Sun Studios in Memphis, TN, birthplace of the mythical careers of both Cash and Presley. Perhaps, inevitably, Furry's star continued to rise and he subsequently established a stand-alone project devoted to The Man in Black called Walkin' With Cash. The group promptly established its own network of fans across the area. "I try to keep it as true to the original as possible," Furry says, "Cash's musical career was over a 50 year span and we cover as much as possible from the memorable 1954 hit single "Hey Porter" to "Rusty Cage" (from the Grammy winning 1996 project "Unchained") and all the heavy hitters in between."
html_data:
Johnny Cash Tribute Band

Cash was a larger than life figure with larger than life faults who loved Jesus and drugs at the same time. He remains one of the only artists to sell over 90 million records. As an inductee of both the Country Music Hall of Fame and the Rock 'n Roll Hall of Fame, Cash helped bridge the generation gap and break down musical barriers.

Walkin' With Cash is a celebration of the life and music of an American icon and an unforgettable tribute to The Man In Black. Keith's love for this legendary entertainer is obvious throughout his show. Cash left some mighty big shoes to fill but when Keith steps up to the microphone and reveals his deep, booming voice, you will swear Cash is back.
short_desc: Walkin' With Cash is a celebration of the life and music of American icon Johnny Cash

name: Rusty Redenbacher
html_data:
In Rusty Redenbacher’s 2 decade plus run of the Indy music scene he has successfully captured the hearts of a progressive arts community on the verge of national super stardom.

His multiple releases with rock collectives Birdmen of Alcatraz and Lazarus, hip-hop groups The Mudkids and Tornado Alley and more have shown the local, regional, and national music scene the extreme versatility and dexterity it takes to be embraced by not only his peers but music lovers of all shapes, sizes, and cross-genre backgrounds.

From the inception of the Birdmen of Alcatraz, to the pre-super stardom scribble jam battles against greats such as Eminem, to the decade long takeover of the Indianapolis Hip-Hop scene by The Mudkids, to the present day where the name Rusty Redenbacher can be heard on WTLC, seen on IMC TV, and deciphered in blog and viral posts felt around the world, the founding member of The Mudkids, Lazarus, and Tornado Alley #ATFU brings you “The Tinkerer”.

Whether it be the thousands of albums Rusty has sold as the head of The Mudkids, the fan admiration and communal support that constantly has voted him as Indy’s Top Artist, the large quantity of free music Rusty had given away to the masses while introducing his #ATFU movement or the vast experiences gained while performing alongside legends including the Wu-Tang Clan, The Roots, Dead Prez, Blackalicious, Atmosphere, and more, one thing that is for certain, legions of Hip-Hop, Rock, Funk, Reggae, and Dubstep fans alike are ready to embrace “The Tinkerer”.
short_desc: Rusty Redenbacher has successfully captured the hearts of the progressive art community on the verge of national super stardom.

html_data:
The ultimate Irish party rock cover band featuring music from Dropkick Murphys, Flogging Molly and other great drinking tunes!

Since the band’s inception in 2009 Red Rebel County has sold out countless shows, been invited to play in front of thousands for various high profile Chicago Police/Fire Department benefits, and packed venues around the Midwest. What began as an excuse for a handful of South Side musicians to get together and play some fun Irish music that defined their musical upbringing, has quickly turned into a nine person ‘tour de force’ that is taking the Midwestern music scene by storm!

Their legion of rabid fans continues to grow rapidly with every show. Covering the pioneers of the bar-room sound, Dropkick Murphys and Flogging Molly, Red Rebel County plays everyone’s favorite party tunes, along with a handful of traditional Irish bar-room tunes and original music that is guaranteed to have the crowd singing and dancing along with the band.

BUT PARTYGOERS BEWARE – this show isn’t for the faint of heart! Red Rebel County doesn’t put on just any old, ordinary show like most other cover bands. When Red Rebel County rolls through a town the venue is quickly transformed into a huge party with the band playing host as your friendly “MC.” So get ready for loads of drinking, toasting, and fans jumping up on stage to sing and dance along with the band at the next show!

Having received national attention and critical acclaim in their respective original Chicago bands, this group is well versed in bringing both energy and musicianship to their live shows. From the bag pipers, to the banjo and the fiddle that will have you dancing along, Red Rebel County puts on a MUST SEE show for music lovers everywhere! Be sure to check them out when the party hits your town! So get ready to raise your glass in a toast, sing and dance along to a song (or ten,) and you’ll have a blast with Red Rebel County…guaranteed!
short_desc: 'Tour de force’ that is taking the Midwestern music scene by storm!
categories: Cover band, Irish party rock, wedding band, festival band

AVM is a Chicago based rock group and recording act headed by singer songwriter and music producer ROBERT MACKEY.

Their innovative musical style is described as "Modern Symphonic Rock"...and played with a passion. Add to that the poignant and evocative vocals of Mackey, a stellar lineup of talented band mates who "play what's best for the song" and you have the makings of a very rare band. Their songs sound fresh, not "cookie cutter" and somehow inspired by the great rock classics.The response to their heart felt and dynamic rock music has become a driving force, resulting in increased international CD sales and rave reviews.

Their LIVE performances are awesome, at times even more powerful than the Album...a rarity for today's bands. This is truly a band that was born to create some amazing rock music and their time has come... For AVM and their rapidly growing base of worldwide fans, it's about the music... JOIN US !
short_desc: AVM is a Chicago based rock group and recording act headed by singer songwriter and music producer ROBERT MACKEY

From the very first note, his music and heart will take you places you've never been. The passion and emotional power that comes from his horn will reach down to the very core of your soul. name: Yuri Lane
html_setlist: Beatbox Harmonica is Yuri's extraordinary talent, which the world began to experience with the birth of YouTube. In fall 2007, his beatbox harmonica video became the number one video on YouTube. This led to live beatbox performances at Google parties around the world, several commercials and the formation of a YouTube community bound by beatbox. When the economic crash led to a slowdown in sponsored appearances, Yuri began work on , a personal journey through the world of YouTube celebrity that confronts issues of authenticity, originality, and self-image through beatbox and live video performance. MeTube premiered at the Chicago Humanities Festival in spring 2010. Yuri hopes to touch just a fraction of his 15 million (but who's counting) YouTube fans with a live show in realtime. He is currently working on 2nd album and a new beatbox show for kids about water.
html_data:
I'm a world renown beatbox performer known around the internet World for playing harmonica and beatboxing at the same time.

Yuri Lane was born on a small island in Holland. His parents, a painter and a violinist, soon moved to San Francisco's Haight-Ashbury district to ride the 70's counter-culture current. Raised in the Haight, Yuri learned rhythm by osmosis and began to breathe beats In the 80's, Yuri started breakdancing and teaching moves at middle school parties. He discovered his true passion in a sixth grade math class where Yuri made sounds to compensate for his lack of skill in arithmetic. When his teacher ordered him to "turn off the radio," Yuri knew that he was on to something. Yuri spent his teenage years on stage at theaters like San Francisco's American Conservatory Theater and Berkeley Repertory Theater while attending high school at the San Francisco School of the Arts. After finishing a theater degree at the Pacific Conservatory for the Performing Arts, Yuri returned to San Francisco to pursue mime, improvisation and alternative theatrical forms.

During the dot-com boom, Yuri found himself as "the geek" in several local and national commercials as well as in TV episodes As San Francisco's boom went bust, Yuri returned to theater and began developing his one-man human beatbox musicalSoundtrack City. Yuri created Soundtrack City by performing one scene at a time at clubs, bars, coffee shops, and small theaters of San Francisco. The full-length production of Soundtrack City debuted in November 2001, with runs in San Francisco and New York in 2002 and a run in Chicago in 2005. Soundtrack City chronicled the transformation of urban neighborhoods during gentrification.

With his partner Sharif Ezzat and his wife Rachel Havrelock, Yuri created "the coolly extraordinary" From Tel Aviv to Ramallah, a hip-hop play that tackles the Israeli-Palestinian conflict.From Tel Aviv to Ramallah steers clear of ideology in order to show the daily lives of young people during the Second Intifada. From Tel Aviv to Ramallah had its world premiere at Theater J in Washington DC in 2003, where it was nominated for a Helen Hayes Award for best new play. The show enjoyed runs in New York, Chicago, San Francisco, Baltimore and Atlanta. It toured across the US at theaters, campuses, and peace events. International venues include Helsinki, London and Jerusalem.
short_desc: I'm a world renown beatbox performer known around the internet World for playing harmonica and beatboxing at the same time.

html_data:
8-Track is a Chicago band that will take you back to the 70’s. An era of platform shoes, bell bottom pants, polyester shirts and, of course, big clunky 8-Track tapes. But most of all, the 70's was an era of great rock & roll! ​We play not only excellent music from the era, but bring a fun, high energy show complete with great musicianship, 70's era wardrobe, and audience participation.

Your customers and/or guests can't help but get up, dance, drink and have a good time. ​8-Track is truly unique in that we play rock tunes only from the 1970's. Music that no other band is playing from bands like Foghat, Aerosmith, Mountain, Nazareth, Grand Funk, Kiss, AC/DC, Alice Cooper, Lynyrd Skynyrd, UFO and Van Halen.

Our resume includes headlining at major clubs such as Austin's Fuel Room, Cubby Bear North and Tilted Kilt (Elgin); being selected as the opening act for legendary bands UFO and Nazareth by promoter Ron Onesti at the Arcada Theater (St. Charles); special performances at Toyota Park, Blarney Island and Cubby Bear (Wrigleyville); and municipal events/festivals including Lisle's Eyes to the Skies, River Grove's Gazebo concert series and Kenilworth's Beach Bash. ​We enjoy being true entertainers who engage and interact with our audiences, and we always play for – rather than to – the crowd.
short_desc: With platform shoes, bell bottom pants, and polyester shirts, 8-Track is a Chicago band that will take you back to the 70’s.

We are a live Cover band that do Pop,Rock,Soul hits that we all know and love & create fun mashups. Our live show is like putting on a party compilation album that covers 80's, 90's, up to today!!!!!

Greg Fulton (formerly of Cyclone Temple and Znowhite) left Chicago and his band “Rebels Without Applause” for Memphis in pursuit of a fresh start and a new life. As a creature of habit, he played in smoky bars and juke joints until the day he met Simon Sunchess, a local club record producer.

Sunchess and the deal he offered seemed legitimate at the time, but Fulton soon realized that it was all smoke and mirrors. After months of dodging Sunchess and his offers, Fulton realized that he no longer wanted to stay in Memphis. Fulton returned to Chicago and as soon as he hit the city limits, he began making phone calls and putting together the hottest band he could find.

Upon hatching his plan, he gave Courtney, Andy, and Rodney the blueprint for Sweet Diezel Jenkins. With the new band set and the plan in motion, Sweet Diezel Jenkins mashes up hits of yesterday and today, adding a heavy hand of backyard feel good party vibe with a dash of gritty juke joint smoky goodness. Using a range of artists from Usher and Kings of Leon, to the Stones and James Brown, the Sweet Diezel Jenkins blueprint was brought to life. It’s gonna be a party y’all!
short_desc: We are a live Cover band that does mashups of Pop, Rock, and Soul hits we all know and love.

html_data: What is Too Much Saturn you ask?! Too Much Saturn is a rock band which plays, what might be best described as, Indie Power Pop. An original mix of melody and hooks consisting of one part indie spirit and two parts pop sensibility – all shaken, not stirred! Memorable, clever and accessible original songs and a few select covers done our way. Served up with soaring harmonies, big drums, 12 string bass, swirling keyboards and a liberal mix of crunchy, ambient and jangly guitars. Refreshing! What they’re saying about our latest CD - "Moving Forward Sideways" Dan Pavelich Kenosha News If you’re a fan of classic guitar pop, Moving Forward Sideways will not disappoint. It’s full of well-written, catchy songs that you’ll want to play again and again. Ice Cream Man Power Pop This Chicago band tick all the right boxes, they have the songs, the tunes, the delivery and some soul too. This is brilliant, another slice of classic power pop. David Bash International Pop Overthrow If you like your power pop tight, with some soulful inflections, you'll absolutely LOVE Too Much Saturn. One listen to their new CD, Moving Forward Sideways, is all it takes to know that these guys can rock it old school! Beverly Paterson Something Else Magazine Too Much Saturn has their own musical vocabulary that stands apart. Teeming with bright and lively tunes, Moving Forward Sideways is sure to win the affection of those partial to harmonious pop rock with an inventively organic twist pointing towards a tightly sealed collection of songs begging to be heard time and time again. Jordan Sovereign Pop Underground This has a classic sound that harkens back to many great bands before them, but they have their own certain charm. Listen and you will soon be singing along with every song. Power Pop Action Moving Forward Sideways - Consistently good songs – Personal favs - "Photogenic" which has a Romantics-like guitar riff and "Funny" – Check them out at www.toomuchsaturn.bandcamp.com SouthSide on the Town Moving Forward Sideways…an eclectic sound surrounding the melodic core of power pop/rock...The entire CD, in it’s own special way, will have you moving… a fresh take in a danceable power pop vibe. Power Popaholic The debut is full of spunky attitude and melodic hooks, with a sound somewhere in between The Lemonheads and The Barenaked Ladies. First rate power pop. Kool Kat Musik Super catchy jangly pop out of the Windy City - Great stuff! Shotgun Solutions Modern power pop with an indie edge.

html_data:
Presenting America's first-ever Steampunk-Country band, BoneWhiskey.

The group can be categorized as a Chicago-based, female-fronted, theatrical country cover band that performs modern country cover tunes with a heavier rock feel and transforms rock and metal covers into country tunes. They present a small dose of commercially viable originals and dress in steampunk attire while using theatrical stage props to provide a high-energy performance with substantial audience engagement.

What this combination offers is a multiple attraction to diverse audience. If you like modern country, steampunk aesthetics, and are attracted to a high-energy performances, BoneWhiskey is comprised of six experienced, professional-minded musicians that will be the perfect addition to your event.

They are capable of short or extended performances. Recent performance venues in Chicagoland include Durty Nellie's, Prairie House Tavern, Club Alibi, J.W. Holstein's, Bannerman's, Port of Blarney, Shark City, and Q-Bar.
short_desc: Presenting America's first-ever Steampunk-Country band, BoneWhiskey. The group can be categorized as a Chicago-based, female-fronted, theatrical country cover band which: a. performs modern country cover tunes with a heavier rock feel; b. transforms rock and metal covers into country tunes; c. presents a small dose of commercially viable originals; d. dresses in steampunk attire; e. uses theatrical stage props; f. provides a high-energy performance with substantial audience engagement. What this combination offers is a multiple attraction to three diverse audiences: (1) those who like modern country, (2) those who enjoy steampunk aesthetics, and (3) those attracted to a high-energy performance. The band is comprised of six experienced, professional-minded musicians. We are capable of short or extended performances. Recent performance venues include Durty Nellie's, Prairie House Tavern, Club Alibi, J.W. Holstein's, Bannerman's, Port of Blarney, and Q-Bar.

name: Buffalo Wabs & The Price Hill Hustle
html_data: Buffalo Wabs & The Price Hill Hustle is a 4 piece, high energy, folk, Americana, old timey, bluegrass influenced outfit that hails from Cincinnati, Ohio. In the relatively short amount of time that the band has been together, they have covered thousands of miles, winning over fans and venues in every town they've played. In the past year, they have shared stages with the likes of Reverend Peyton's Big Damn Band, Steep Canyon Rangers, Town Mountain, Jesco White, Spirit Family Reunion, Dom Flemons of The Carolina Chocolate Drops and many others. They have been invited to many festivals and events in the region, including Buckle Up, Whispering Beard Folk Festival, Duck Creek Log Jam, Paddlefest, Taste of Cincinnati and more. Being from Cincinnati has afforded them the luxury of being within a couple hours of many other cities that have their own vibrant music scenes. The band hits the road every chance they get. They are currently averaging 12 to 15 shows a month, and show no signs of slowing down. Every time they return to a town, the crowds get bigger, more CDs end up in the hands of fans, and word of mouth spreads even further. "The Hustle", as they're often referred to, is currently recording a full length record that will be released in spring of 2015. We provide a very fun, high energy show and bring smiles to audiences of all ages.
short_desc: Buffalo Wabs & The Price Hill Hustle is a 4 piece, high energy, folk, Americana, old timey, bluegrass influenced outfit that hails from Cincinnati, Ohio.

Miro Swing is a Chicago-based jazz ensemble. Our professional musicians have many years experience performing at both public and private events. Our specialty is jazz manouche, also commonly referred to as gypsy jazz. Django Reinhardt and Stéphane Grappelli were quintessential in starting this genre.  The typical lineup for this genre consists of two guitars, upright bass, and melodic instruments such as violin, clarinet, mandolin, and trumpet. 

The experience of our expert musicians allows for music in other genres as well, including Traditional/Dixieland, Bebop, Hard Bop, and Cool Jazz.
short_desc: Swang Gypsy Jazz performances are ideal for both private and public performances.

The smooth, harmonic sounds of a cappella group Sunday Afternoon is reminiscent of a perfect Sunday Afternoon-energetic yet relaxing, familiar yet unique to each person’s experience, with a family friendly vibe. The award winning group has been wowing audiences across the U.S for years performing at a variety of venues and events, from state fairs and wine tastings, to ball parks and national music festivals.

Sunday Afternoon has nabbed a spot as one of the 8 best A cappella groups in the Midwest the past two years from the national Harmony Sweepstakes music festival. While the group has gained national acclaim, they haven’t forgotten their roots being heavily involved with JDRF, The Boys and Girls Club and many other organizations in their home town of Cedar Rapids, IA.

Sunday Afternoon incorporates various musical genres into each performance, providing each audience member the chance to leave their performances completely satisfied.
