html_data: One Season spawned from the late-night lasagna basement musings of gig-buddies Chris Harris and Tim Bernard, both avid song-writing vocalists and guitarists. In late 2011, recorded an EP “As Bad as It Gets” at Rax Trax Studios, sighting that they just wanted to get together and record some music at a time when the state of the world felt like things couldn’t get any worse. Using “As Bad as It Gets” as momentum to find like-minded musicians and play shows around the Chicago area, One Season eventually rounded out the lineup with drummer Chris Close and bassist Scott Tooredman. Channeling inspired outbursts of songwriting, comedic episodes, and uncanny jams, One Season has honed a sound that is influenced by a wide variety of sounds. One Season is “Omni-Rock”, an eclectic concoction consisting of a blues-rock and alternative-rock foundation that’s salted with soul, funk, and pop sensibilities. Contributing to this sound is a duo of dynamic lead singers, big harmonies, inspired guitar-work, and undulating vibrations from the rhythm section. A One Season performance is a rousing experience that leaves crowds chanting for one more song at the end of their sets. The band is so dedicated to the music that they will play through smoke, fire alarms, hustling & bustling farmers’ market crowds, and biker rallies to keep the Omni-Rock alive. One Season has continued to light up cornerstone Chicago venues, including Metro, Double Door, Subterranean, the Cubby Bear, Lincoln Hall, and even the House of Blues and the Hard Rock Cafe, since emerging onto the local music scene with a take-no-prisoners attitude. So, whether it’s a one-show tour to New Orleans, a wrestling gig in the suburbs, a naval base performance, a Six Flags all-day event, the open mic around the corner, or a revered music venue, One Season is sure to give fans a genuinely sensational experience. One Season recently released an EP in late 2014 entitled Man on a Mission, which can be found on iTunes, Google Play, Pandora, Spotify, CD Baby, etc.
short_desc: A diverse blues-based Rock band from Chicago, Illinois.

html_data: Humphrey-McKeown is an original Americana (Folk/Rock) band based in the Chicago area. The Humphrey-McKeown (HM) songwriting partnership began in 2006 between New York native, Heather Humphrey and Chicago-based, Tom McKeown. Before long, they were writing for publishers in Nashville, Chicago and LA. Combining Heather’s innate sense of melody with Tom’s pursuit of something new and unexpected. HM wrote for any occasion and in any style; always seeking to better themselves and their craft. When asked “How do you write a better song?” their answer has always been “That’s easy…we write another song.” After penning over 100 songs for others, Tom & Heather turned their focus on writing for their own musical voice. Putting together all the pieces to create a great live band, HM brought in “big-beat” drummer/percussionist Jim Livas. Jim then introduced them to bassist extraordinaire Tony Meadors and Tony in turn introduced them to virtuoso violinist/fiddler Jeff Teppema. Incredibly, Tony and Jeff ’s individual auditions actually became the final tracks on the fourth CD “All I Wanted to Hear.” HM’s latest release confirms that their musical puzzle is now complete. “From the first note we played together, we all knew this was the sound we had been searching for.” ~ Tom McKeown Over four albums HM has been perfecting their mix of experimental folk, upbeat pop with a hint of progressive music and Brill Building songwriting. This combination has created the HM flavored contemporary folk-rock, Americana sound. They begin by weaving together intricate layers of acoustic guitar, mandolin, piano, fiddle and bass and then drop a ten-ton drum kit on top of it. Folk-Rock… with a huge beat and brilliant musicianship. But as great as the music is, HM still puts the primary focus on the voices and the lyrics. “It’s not OK for us to just write catchy tunes. It’s more important to create a memory for those who listen – whether it’s soaring or heart-ache, it’s creating that emotional moment.” ~ Heather Humphrey Tom and Heather’s combined lead vocals breathe magic into the songs. Their voices are perfectly matched through quiet acoustic ballads, playful pop and edgy "swampgrass” rock. Humphrey ~ McKeown “Great tunes appear to come naturally them and their songs invariably come loaded with plentiful hooks and the kind of choruses that stick around.” ~ Leicester Bangs, UK “Tried and tested, yet fresh sounding male-female medley reaching across the expanse of lush tracks. Diverse instruments – each featuring and acoustic twang- the formula works! Tender and heart-warming… great lyrics and guitar-work.” ~Spy District Humphrey-McKeown has been featured on WXRT, WDCB, WZRD and fearless radio.
short_desc: Humphrey-McKeown is an original Americana (Folk/Rock) band based in the Chicago area.

html_setlist: Electric set Smells Like Teen Spirit You Know You’re Right Rape Me Breed Territorial Pissings Aneurysm Sliver Been A Son In Bloom Polly Dumb Come As You Are About A Girl Heart Shaped Box All Apologies On A Plain Something in the Way Lithium Sappy Even in His Youth Negative Creep Frances Farmer Will Have Her Revenge on Seattle Acoustic set: Special requests for other songs/b sides including MTV UNPLUGGED only upon special request/private functions.
html_data: Smells Like Nirvana is Chicago’s grungiest tribute to Nirvana playing songs from the albums Bleach, Incesticide, Nevermind, In Utero and MTV Unplugged. Composed of seasoned pros and DIE-HARD FANS of Nirvana, Smells Like Nirvana’s live tribute to Nirvana is a haunting episode of grunge filled angst and rock prowess. Smells Like Nirvana is one of Chicago's newest up and coming tribute acts! They are captivating the hearts of Nirvana fans night after night, show after show. You definitely want to watch Smells Like Nirvana live as they recreate the legendary sounds of Nirvana. Few bands in rock history have had a more immediate and connectable impact on their contemporary rock musical landscape than Nirvana did in the early nineties and 20 years later Smells Like Nirvana is capturing and re-creating the heart felt angst and passion of Nirvana night after night, performance after performance. Why did SMELLS LIKE NIRVANA get started? Smells Like Nirvana is an attempt at honoring Nirvana’s Legacy by staying true to the mechanics of what Nirvana was all about which was being a real organic rock band. No click tracks or backing tracks, what you hear is what you get and that’s loud angst guitars and drums coupled with a passionate trio on stage remembering the late great Kurt Cobain. It’s been 20 years since the original line up of Nirvana has taken the stage and it’s sad to think of the loss of the legend Kurt Cobain who unfortunately took his own life at 27, joining club 27 with such artists at Janis Joplin, Jimi Hendrix and Jim Morrison. In no shape or form is the Chicago Nirvana Tribute ’Smells like Nirvana’ trying to replace Nirvana; THAT’S IMPOSSIBLE. No one can replace Nirvana. Smells Like Nirvana is a celebration of Nirvana, three die hard fans of Nirvana sharing their love of Nirvana.
short_desc: Smells Like Nirvana is Chicago’s grungiest tribute to Nirvana playing songs from the albums Bleach, Incesticide, Nevermind, In Utero and MTV Unplugged.

html_data: BomBBone is Chicago based world punk rock band ,with high energy live shows, party feeling and songs sung in three , sometimes four different languages. BomBBone’s live performance is bound to be a surprise for many in the audience. Recently called “Gypsy Punks, Balkan Pimps”, BomBBone delivers a powerful performance that reverberates with lament for lost domains, for times passed. This punk avant-garde production brings to the stage both of the lost worlds – the Balkan eulogy and punk protest in a unique live show filled with energy and masterful music craft. BomBBone combines music with a love of paradox and an idiosyncratic, sometimes outrageous, sense of humor, thus making it the most puzzling, provocative, humorous and profound show you are yet to see.
short_desc: BomBBone is Chicago based world punk rock band ,with high energy live shows, party feeling and songs sung in three , sometimes four different languages.

name: Krystal Metcalfe
html_data:
Bold, Confident and more Fearless than ever. 

These words, and more, describe the fiercely talented Krystal Metcalfe. 

This Chicagoan, by way of St. Louis artist puts her life experiences, musicianship, and love for people on her chest and is always ready to set the nearest stage on fire. 

Her love for music runs deep into her roots and she uses those seeds to share real, purposeful, and meaningful music that will uplift your spirits and also move the crowd. “I perform to connect with my audience. By sharing music, I hope to create ‘Escapism’ for them. Take them away from their stresses, problems, and worries, if even only for a moment,” says Metcalfe. 

Her musical style described as “the love child of Aretha Franklin and Chaka Kahn, infused with Indie pop and Musical Theatre” though abstract, proves to be a winning combination for this artist. She has been recognized by The Chicago Tribune's Redeye as 1 of the top 15 artist to watch for 2015, as well as highlighted by Jet magazine as a new artist spotlight with her new single 'To Be Loved'.

With a soon to come EP, slated for release mid 2015, and many more magical happenings, Krystal Metcalfe is a rising star ready to do her part to change the world, one stage at a time.
short_desc: Bold, Confident and more Fearless than ever. These words, and more, describe the fiercely talented Krystal Metcalfe.

html_setlist: Can be provided. Negotiable.
html_data: My name is Daniel Weisberg. I am a Hip-Hop artist and rapper. I have written and helped produce two mix-tapes. I have performed at a variety of venues as well as been on an IHeart radio talk show. I perform weekly at open mics along with any other opportunities that present themselves. I am 20 years old, from Chicago, Illinois, and a college student.  Ever since I was a child, I have been in love with music. I grew up listening to The Spinners, Frank Sinatra and the Gypsy Kings due to my grandparents influence. During my early childhood, I was mainly inspired by Michael Jackson and would sing and dance his music all day and night.  I performed on stage at a restaurant and a couple of parties and every other opportunity I received. I got a lot of love after each event! It wasn’t until my junior year of high school that I realized I wanted to make a career out of music! I lived in Puerto Rico for three years where I was exposed to different kinds of music. This led me to broaden my musical taste even further. After returning to the States, I realized music was my passion. One night, my friend told me that due to the competition, focusing on being a rapper would be a waste of time and that I could do something more time useful, like journalism, due to my love of sports. Ever since then, I told myself I would prove him and anyone else wrong. I would be that one of 100,000 that make it as a rapper, and 1 of 1,000,000 that make it as a successful musician!  I have always loved music, and I began to become more diverse while learning more history.  I started listening to soul and funk from the 50s, R&B from the 60s, and many old school rap artists.  I originally heard a lot of these songs with my grandparents so they were a bit familiar to me.  As I got older, Michael Jackson was and always will be my inspiration, but I have other inspirations also.  Some of these include: Tupac Shakur, Eminem, Jackson 5, and the Spinners.  My goal is to be one of the most successful and diverse entertainers of all time.  I want to be the greatest rapper and branch out to have a fantastic future in singing, dancing and acting.  I feel I am unique in Hip Hop because I do not curse in any of the music that I make and all of my music is relevant to my current lifestyle, thought process, and the world around me.  I take what I learn from older professionals, and I make my own style, trying to incorporate a variety of beats and musical styles. In my recent mixtape that dropped on Valentine’s Day called “Grind Harder,” I talk about very deep subject matter, from the death of my grandmother to the violence of black on black crime.  I am always writing and have released a single since then. I no longer have dreams, I only have goals, and my goal is on a great path with my current sophomore year attendance at Columbia College Chicago.  I look forward to working with you!

html_data:
Meet Bernard Scavella

Let Bernard Scavella take you on a journey across music genres, one saxophone tune at a time. Delight your auditory senses when you listen to the cool, jazzy stylings of Bernard Scavella, a jazz saxophonist based in South Holland, Illinois. As a skilled musician who has been on the scene for more than 50 years, I take pride in sharing my talent for tenor, alto, and soprano saxophone compositions to music lovers everywhere. Inspired by the sounds of jazz greats, such as Joe Henderson, Dexter Gordon, John Coltrane, and Sonny Rollins, my favorite aspect of performing is expressing myself musically while enticing you with smooth, timeless sounds and music.

I started my music career studying under the great Joe Henderson throughout my teenage years. Thanks in large part to his influences, I have also had the pleasure of performing alongside recognized names, Billy Cobham and George Cables, as a co-founder of the New York City based Jazz group, The Jazz Samaritans.

 Recordings & Live Shows

 Having honed my skills as a band leader and sideman, I served as the principle arranger and saxophonist of the jazz group The Groovemasters during the 1970s and '80s. More recently in 2008, I assumed the leader's role during the recording of 'Bout Time: Volumes I & II. I also released a new solo album in March of 2014, A Taste of Scavella. My other performances have included a number of appearances at the Chicago and Hyde Park Jazz Festivals and the ETA Creative Arts Foundation.

A Taste of Scavella cd has been climbing the charts at Jazz Week, Currently is listed in the Top 50 at #33.

Saxophonist who plays various genres of music: Jazz, Fusion, Swing, Hard Bop, Be-Bop,Bossa Nova/Latin. Have performed for Corporate special events; weddings; school seminars; private events; jazz concerts. 

Member of American Federation of Musicians
Member of Chicago Federation of Musicians

html_data: HINGE is a powerful, versatile high energy cover band from the western suburbs of Chicago. From their humble beginning, they have emerged from the proving grounds to be one of the most entertaining cover bands playing the local suburban circuit today. They cover the popular mainstream music from the 70s / 80s classic rock of Journey, Triumph, Boston, Bon Jovi, Led Zeppelin and Foreigner to the current hits of Maroon 5, STP, Fall Out Boy, Imagine Dragons and Walk the Moon just to name a few. In addition to keeping their popular list growing, they also add their own twist and touch to the music while keeping the identifiable spirit of the song intact; you'll know every song within the first 5 seconds. Their list has proven the test of time, stays well-balanced, powerful and most of all... entertaining fun which attributes to the success and their increasing fan base With that wide range of music, they can honestly say 'we've got it covered... there's sure to be something for everyone..." "...if you've heard it on the radio, there's a good chance we're playing it..."

html_data: A rootsy rock quartet with a touch of jam-band soul, Avon Dale features a dynamic rhythm section, the elemental sounds of an acoustic guitar, blues-inspired riffs, and vocals that range from tender and plaintive to gritty and beseeching. A powerful live act, Avon Dale combines well-crafted indie rock tunes with lengthy improvisational jams. With a raw, energetic presence, Avon Dale has quickly become a must-see act. After graduating from the Univ. of Illinois, three of the band members decided to hit the road and pursue their musical aspirations in Memphis. With the addition of a Memphis-based bass player, the band has played shows from Michigan to Colorado. In October of 2014, they recorded their first studio EP Dress It Up at Ardent Studios. They tour extensively, playing clubs and festivals throughout the Mid-West.

html_setlist: Sample Opening Act Set List Somebody to Love, Jefferson Airplane Conflicted, original by Fire The Canon Crimson n Clover, Joan Jett and the Blackhearts Creep, Radiohead Everlong, Foo Fighters Poison, original by Fire The Canon Rock n Roll, Led Zeppelin Stars come from, original by Fire The Canon Sample Other Set List: Cherub Rock Say it Aint So Crimson n Clover Celebrity Skin The Middle Closingtime All of Me Somebody To Love Eye of the Tiger Times Like These Im a Believer Creep Hey Jude Rope Welcome To Paradise I Wanna Be A Rockstar (Nippersank) Beverly Hills Teen Spirit Heartbreaker Everlong Rock N Roll Stars Come From
html_data: Jefferson Airplane, Weezer, Pat Benetar, Joan Jett, Foo Fighters, The Beatles, Survivor, Green Day, RadioHead and more... Rock with a slight Tilt?! Would someone please Fire The Canon! Yes! We spelled "Canon" instead of "Cannon" to reflect the musical term, "Canon". Just trying to be creative. Fire The Canon! Up and coming teen band... Performing family friendly classic rock, modern rock and originals including their original song "DONUT GIRL". "DONUT GIRL" was written upon lead guitarist Andrew buying donuts and a cute girl wrote her number on the back of his receipt. He later texted the number and got no reply. She eventually attended a show but informed the hopeful young rocker that she got a boyfriend and was no longer available. Leading to the plea "DoNut break my heart". Hopes of dating "Donut Girl" will live on in song. "DONUT GIRL" will be available later this summer on Fire The Canons debut cd... soon to be available on itunes, spotify, Amazon and more. Lead Guitar & Vocals Andrew Gallagher was born in Chicago. His mom a professional singer and his dad a drummer. Andrews first real experience in music was when his father took him to a Peter Gabriel Concert when he was four years old. Andrew grew up listening to Peter Gabriel, Genesis, The Foo Fighters, Led Zeppelin, and Coldplay, which were mostly a direct influence of his father. Andrew started out playing the drums when he was four, but never got very attached to them. When Andrew was 6 he got his first guitar from his grandparents along with a DVD Tutorial. He struggled with it at such a young age. He later picked it up again in 6th grade after taking a music class. He grabbed his old guitar and used YouTube to learn. His Great Uncle then gave him an old acoustic guitar that Andrew played until he bought his first electric guitar. The summer after his freshman year of High School, Drew put together a band with him as the lead guitarist and singer, a friend as the bass player, and his brother Ryan Gallagher on drums, but his friend quit the band due to creative differences. He then turned to another friend, Ryan King and asked if he would join. After one jam session they were set and performed at a small party with some friends. Later Tristan Abrams joined as the lead vocalist and Drew became the lead guitar player. This is the band we know today. Drew continues to rock his heart out and pursue his passion for music. Bass Guitar Ryan King began listening to music from a very early age, especially rock, since his Dad is an avid listener and piano and guitar player. Ryan developed an ear for the guitar and started tinkering around with an acoustic when he was 9 years old. His interest to learn brought an excellent guitar teacher, Marco, in to his life. With weekly lessons and lots of jam sessions with his dad, Ryan gained a love for all kinds of music and the desire to play both acoustic and electric guitars. It didn’t take long for Ryan to discover his true passion, the bass guitar. Which he played in High school Jazz band. With his quiet demeanor, Ryan felt the rhythm of music and began to hone his skills on the bass by the age of 13. His major influences have, so far, been primarily his father and the bass guitarist from his favorite band, Rush. Ryan would say that his greatest decision so far in life has been joining forces with Andrew and Ryan Gallagher and Tristan Abrams to form the band Fire The Canon. Ryan loves doing his signature jumping and behind the head playing moves for the fans. Drums Ryan Gallagher he brings the BOOM! to Fire The Canon! Ryan started banging on the drums at the age of 2 with some help from his Dad... He is influenced by Genesis and Phil Collins as well as Neil Peart and John Bonham. Sometimes we think he has John Bonham trapped in his body! He may look little but he does Big things! Vocals & Guitar Tristan Jewel Abrams is a true Rock star. Born to musician parents, given a stage name “Tristan Jewel” from birth, some could say she was born of music. She has been around music her entire existence and took some of her first steps backstage among Rock Legends such as The GrassRoots, Ides of March and Peter Noone. Theaters and Stages are more like Home to her, where Sound Engineers and Stage Crew become her family. As a toddler she would mimic her Dads (Bob Abrams, formerly of The Buckinghams) stage moves with a little red guitar and put on shows for her siblings and in her front yard. Tristan started playing piano at age 3, singing and playing guitar at age 7, bass guitar at age 10, and Saxophone at age 12. She has been a composer and ASCAP writer since age 7. Her elementary teacher Mr. Ortman played Charlie Parker in class where Tristan fell in love with Jazz, it encouraged her to follow in her Grandfather, Bob Abrams Sr., Mother and Fathers footsteps of Jazz training. Tristan Jewel attended The Music Institute of Chicago where she was one of the youngest students in the Adult Jazz Studies Program. Tristan has also had the privilege of recording in studios such as Engine Studios and playing venues such as The Metro in Chicago with Girls Rock at the age of 11 and again at age 12. Tristan bought her first Vinyl Album from Jonas Grigola at the Chicagoland Record Show when she was about 12 years old, it was Jefferson Airplane, "Flight Log" and now she is singing her own version of "Somebody To Love" with Fire The Canon! More recently Tristan as a vocalist has opened at the Arcada Theatre for Acts such as Jefferson Starship. She has also performed Jazz shows with greats such as Wayne Messmer. She is excited about and loves her band brothers in Fire The Canon! Nothing but great things in the future.
short_desc: Band Members are ages 12-16! Not Your Average Teen Band!  Classic Rock, Rock & Originals. Up to 3 hours of material.

name: Sydney Jay
html_data: Looking for great, musical live entertainment? R&B, Pop, and Soul Songtress Sydney Jay is your match! Bio: Singer/Songwriter Sydney Jay was born in Montgomery, AL, and raised up in the “Windy City” of Chicago, IL. She emerged onto the music scene in the late 2000’s as an independent artist, searching for opportunities that would help her leverage in a highly competitive music industry. The soulful songstress was first acknowledged by Chicago’s #1 radio station WGCI; in their “Chicago Teen Idol” showcase. Without a doubt, Sydney blew the judges away with her incredible voice winning WGCI'S Chicago Idol competition! Since then, she has been grinding it out performing at various events around the city hoping to be discovered by the right person one day. Sydney’s passion for music is authentic and her lyrical flow uplifts those who are within her presense. Her most recent feature with mainstream artist Mayo on their single “Memories,” captivated over 99.7k plays within a month of circulation. As an independent artist, Sydney has managed to navigate her way throughout the Chicago-land market in-front & behind the scenes. Performing vocals for many notable artists such as: Mayo, Jack Red, and Chicago's own Chance The Rapper. With her recent hit single titled “ Same Page” circulating the Internet; it's already gained over 27.7k plays within a two month time frame. She’s been featured on Dj Booth, Intice, Smooth Waves, and more! It's only a matter of time before she reaches national caliber, and becomes the next RnB legend.
short_desc: Looking for great, musical live entertainment? R&B, Pop, and Soul Songtress Sydney Jay is your match!

html_data: Singer, songwriter, guitarist and poet, Philadelphia Phil, combines lively ragtime and fingerstyle blues interpretations of traditional Americana with original blues poems, songs and stories for a unique and engaging acoustic performance. Philadelphia Phil spent his childhood in Paris, France, Biloxi, Mississippi, Atlanta, Georgia and Swanton, Vermont, before landing in the steel mill town of Coatesville, Pennsylvania, where he grew up in the smokestack shadows of blue collar America. Escaping high school he made Philadelphia his home, alternating between the turf that gave the world John Coltrane, Philly Joe Jones and Stanley Clark, and cities across America, living for a time in Buffalo, New Orleans, Fort Worth, even Iowa, before settling in the Heartland. Most recently Philadelphia Phil has appeared at: Crow's Nest (Cincinnati, OH) Red Barn Radio (Lexington, KY) Southgate House Revival (Newport, KY) Edinburgh Pixie Theater (Edinburgh, IN) Carmel Porchfest (Carmel, IN) Central Pennsylvania Festival of Art and Music (State College, PA) The Chatterbox Jazz Club (Indianapolis, IN) The HIFI (Indianapolis, IN) Journeyman Distillery (Three Oaks, MI) Maifest Music & Art Festival (Covington, KY) The Saloon at The Seasons Lodge (Nashville, IN) Getaway Hostel (Chicago, IL) Gaslight Inn (Indianapolis, IN) Silvie's Lounge (Chicago, IL) The Elbo Room (Chicago, IL) Pure Eatery (Indianapolis, IN) Art Squared (Indianapolis, IN) Playing For Change Day 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014 (Indianapolis, IN) Birdy's (Indianapolis, IN) Zinc (Cleveland, OH) Chicago Acoustic Underground (Chicago, IL) Refuge Coffee Bar (Cincinnati, OH) Brylan's (Cincinnati, OH) Metamora Old Time Music Festival (Metamora, IN) Common Grounds Coffee House (Lexington, KY) The Hub Cafe and Tapas Bar (Danville, KY) Red Lion Grog House (Indianapolis, IN) Zazoo's Bar (Louisville, KY) Beatniks Cafe (Marion, IN) Doc's Music Hall (Muncie, IN) All Nations Bed and Breakfast (Indianapolis, IN) Firefly Cafe (Fort Wayne, IN) Aroma Cafe (Champaign, IL) Highlands Taproom (Louisville, KY) Piasa Winery (Grafton, IL) It's All About Wine (Springfield, IL) Firenczi (Warrensburg, IL) Creekside Cultural Center (Lenhartsville, PA) Coffee Cafe (Media, PA) Barrington Coffee House (Barrington, NJ) Bullfrog Brewery (Williamsport, PA) John and Peter's (New Hope, PA) Indy's Jukebox (Indianapolis, IN) Muddy Boots Cafe (Nashville, IN) Red Lion Grog House (Indianapolis, IN) Art Bank (Indianapolis, IN) Melody Inn (Indianapolis, IN) City Market (Indianapolis, IN) Gumbo Aid (Indianapolis, IN)

American Idiots is a raw exciting tribute to the mighty Green Day, bringing the same energy and drive as when you first saw them hit the MTV video scene.Opening with show stoppers Blink getting the crowd ready to rock and playing all the hits.Perfect show for Casinos,Festivals and Big Events Book Us Now! One of the most iconic bands to come out of the 90s is pop punk phenomenon Green Day. Their songs with hook filled lyrics have top the charts for 2 decades. Sold out arenas and world tours and even a Tony award winning Broadway play puts this band into a status only few can dream to attain. The American Idiots bring it back every show,is the closest thing to a live Green Day show. Blink-182 were the unexpected 1990s pop-punk band into the mainstream. The trio emerged from a skate-punk culture with a high-energy stage show heavy with slapstick and fart jokes. But like the slightly older Green Day, closer study revealed hook-filled rock songs obsessed with breakup and loneliness. They have sold out arenas and world tours.Blink-182 has sold over twelve million albums in the United States and over 35 million albums worldwide..Blink is the next best thing, closest to the real Blink.

html_setlist: Olivia Dvorak performs many of her original songs, and of course, a variety of fan favorites such as Miranda Lambert, KT Tunstall, Fleetwood Mac, and even Jackson 5. Olivia's show is an experience that keeps her audience entertained from a high energy hour set, or through the journey of a 3 hour show. Using her custom looper pedal set up and intricate guitar skills, she is truly the essence of a one man band.
html_data: Artist | Singer | Songwriter | Guitarist | Performer Olivia Dvorak is a songwriter and artist whose unique songs, lyrics, and intricate guitar playing led her to professionally record in Nashville, TN at Treasure Isle Recorders with some of the top musicians in the city. Her unique country style pours into genres such as rock, blues, Celtic, and folk. Since she recorded, Olivia has won two RAMI Awards for Artist of the Year and Song of the Year, played at one of Nashville’s iconic venues, the Bluebird Cafe, has been a guest speaker for several inspirational youth events, and has directly supported country music’s legendary Loretta Lynn, Scotty McCreery, Jana Kramar, Drake Bell, Trace Adkins, and the Band Perry. Surrounded by a family of musicians, Olivia began her journey by singing when she was able to talk and begging to take piano lessons before her hands were big enough to reach the keys. After taking six years of piano lessons from her mom, Olivia's dad helped her discover the instrument that she would soon fall in love with for the remainder of her career: the guitar. At ten years old, she was strumming chords, picking melodies, leading worship at church, and performing Celtic music in her family's band. Songwriting was never in the forefront of her mind, but the emotions of junior high brought out a gift in Olivia that would soon propel her to places that she never thought she would go. What started off as simple songs about life, relationships, and experiences, soon matured into tunes that began to touch people from the ages of five years old to fifty. As the young artist walked across the stage to receive her High School diploma, her path led her straight to Bradley University to pursue a major in Graphic Design. After a year of art classes, writing songs in her spare time, playing too loud in her dorm room, and then winning Bradley's "Idol Competition," Olivia realized that her heart was leading her towards a life of music entertainment. At the end of her freshman year, the nineteen year old’s experience at a Keith Urban concert was enough to launch her straight to a songwriter's festival in Nashville. Olivia explained, "I was amazed that one person could touch a whole stadium of people with a three minute song... I knew in that moment that I needed to do the same thing." That summer, only a week in Nashville allowed Olivia to meet the former manager of the Beach Boys and current owner of Treasure Isle Recorders, Fred Vail. Alongside of her parents, Fred began to push the soon the be country star through an intense summer of writing, and a week of recording in the studio. The extreme focus, dedication, and sacrifice that the aspiring musician practiced when she laid down the tracks for her album "Don't Come Knockin,'" has not wavered. Once the summer ended and the recording sessions were under raps, Olivia decided to hone in on her craft by earning a commercial music degree at Greenville College in Southern Illinois. During a semester of barely passing music theory, working hard at ear training, and exploring the world of Classical voice, she decided to take a leap of faith with the undying support of her parents. At twenty years old, Olivia completely dropped out of college in the winter of 2013 because she felt so strongly about immersing herself in the music business outside of school. Building a career from the ground up would prove to be a long, rigorous journey for the entrepreneur as she went to every open mic she could, played for free at coffee shops, and quickly moved up to bar gigs, private parties, and weddings. "If I don't learn every single aspect of how to make a living by performing, managing myself, booking my own shows, and doing the dirty work, how will I know how to be a professional in this crazy industry?" the songwriter stated. As she perfected her skills, professionalism, and songwriting over the course of a couple years, Olivia met her current sound engineer, Jeremy Rollefson, who helped the process of developing her unique live sound along with her dad. With the encouragement and love from her family, friends, and ever-supporting fans, the talented singer/songwriter received an opportunity in the spring of 2015 that would change the course of her entire career. Boldly strumming her guitar, and singing with more passion than anyone had heard in years from a twenty-two year old girl, Olivia took the stage to directly open for Country's original female star, Loretta Lynn. The whole audience at the Arcada Theater immediately connected with the young performer's personality, performance and songs. "The most important thing I can do as a songwriter is to place my hand into the deepest crevices of my heart. This allows me to discover specific truths about myself in order to have a general understanding of the human heart as a whole. Each song I write needs to be honest, relatable, and strong." A true artist, songwriter, and lover of other people, Olivia makes her goal in life to write songs that simply take people with her on her journey.
short_desc: Artist | Singer | Songwriter | Guitarist

Darrin Johnson Hypnosis Unplugged Comedy Show Alluring, Entertaining, Inspiring, Edgy and Unconventional: Darrin Johnson’s ability to captivate an audience (both large and small) – with just one touch, is simply mind blowing. “The science of hypnosis has always been intriguing to me, but to see how Darrin takes command of the stage is incredibly impressive.

As a master of his craft, he brings a new level of entertainment that I’ve never seen before.” With a unique talent to tap into the subconscious, Darrin Johnson’s approach to hypnosis is truly one-of-a-kind. He utilizes both the power of positive visualization and subliminal science, to move his participants into a higher level of unconscious thinking. His unique approach, truly allows his participants to “unplug” from the world around them and to tap into subconscious thoughts, feelings and desires.

As a certified Hypnotist, with a degree in Alternative Medicine, his expertise has allowed him to work with a vast array of clients, including: executives, professional athletes and students. His shows are highly entertaining – a MUST SEE!”

html_data: Foline Roos is a singer-songwriter whose soulful, theatrical style has been deeply enriched by her musical collaborations throughout the years. Although she is a lover of various music genres, she is most deeply influenced by jazz, musical theatre and pop. Foline, a theatre geek in school, was cast in such musicals as “Cabaret,” “Oklahoma” and “Once on This Island.” At the age of 11, her first demo received airplay on Chicago's Hip Hop radio station, WGCI. A native of Chicago, Foline spent her late teens conscientiously recording demos with various producers, including Earl Powell, who is best known for his collaboration with singer Jennifer Hudson. It was at this time that Foline first began to develop her talent and passion for songwriting, incorporating pop elements with her soulful sound . Later she met Sue Carey and the late Karena Mendoza, both of whom cast her in the principal role in their musical collaboration, “Africa & Plumbridge,” which won the New York International Fringe Festival award for best songwriting. Sue and Karena, each a classically trained opera singer, grew to be Foline's mentors and helped her further develop a more theatrical sound and presence for the stage. Foline was recently seen performing “Urinetown” the musical at Munroe Park Theatre Guild in Chicago last spring. In addition, she has a newly-recorded demo-which includes two songs she wrote under the direction of saxophonist and arranger Roy McGrath.
short_desc: Foline Roos is a singer-songwriter whose soulful, theatrical style has been deeply enriched by her musical collaborations throughout the years.

Rhythm Method is a seven-piece, energetic rock cover band. They perform hit classic songs and deep tracks from the '60s (Beatles, Stones, Zeppelin), '70s-'80s (Petty, Mellencamp, Springsteen, Queen, Van Morrison, Paul Simon), '90s (Cake, Sublime, Weezer), and much more. Based on the North Side of Chicago, the band consists of piano, guitar, bass, drums, and brass. 


We play wonderful songs of the past the way they should be played in the present. No silly outfits. No rapid-fire medleys. No ironic covers. No gimmicks. Just great music played by great musicians.


Eric Nyberg: Vocals, piano, guitar
Vince Versaci: Guitar, vocals, harmonica
Adam Schaal: Bass, vocals
Dave Doyle: Drums

Rhythm Method's friend and fan base is strong, as the members are all local young professionals in their twenties/thirties, playing in and around the city. This past year, Rhythm Method performances regularly brought in a crowd of over 100 audience members. Recent shows include Hard Rock Cafe, Abbey Pub, Cubby Bear, Elbo Room, Uptown Lounge, Goose Island, Reggies, HVAC, Mothers, and more. html_data:
The Sonic Poets feature Dave Grilly - sax and woodwinds, Michael Hershenson - guitars, Jeff Kier - piano, Lanny Grilly – drums, Brian Sandstrom – bass.

The group members have a long history in Jazz – they’ve played with, or shared the stage with jazz greats, such as Ahmad Jamal, Herbie Hancock, Sonny Stitt, Elvin Jones, Buster Williams, Willie Pickens, Henry Johnson, Chuck Webb, Dave Liebman, Bill Evans, Mose Allison, Judy Roberts, Hal Russell, John Campbell, Hoagy Carmichael, Frank D’Rone, Howard Levy, Rusty Jones, Robert Shy, Mark Walker, Mayo Tiana, James Sanders, Fareed Haque, Ghalib Ghallab, Larry Novak, Larry Coryell, Tina Turner…just to name a few.

They are called upon to play as guest artists at universities, such as The University Of Chicago, Triton College, Northeastern University, and Roosevelt University.

The members have played across the U.S. from The Lion’s Share in San Francisco, The Desert Inn in Las Vegas, The Jazz Showcase & The Green Mill in Chicago, Smalls in Greenwich Village, as well as internationally – in Japan, Rome, Paris, and Tel-Aviv. 

The Sonic Poets perform pianist Jeff Kier's jazz compositions. Mark Stevens, a San Francisco DJ, commented that "Jeff was emerging as one of the great composers of our time."

Their last CD, "Goin' Places!” by Jeff Kier & The Grilly Brothers, on the BluJazz label, was Grammy Recognized in 2009. The Sonic Poets current show combines Jeff's indelible melodies and the band’s unique fusion of solid grooves and seductive world-rhythms.

Much of Jeff Kier's music has been scored for both Symphony & Jazz Orchestras. Examples recorded live at The Jazz Showcase can be found under the "Orchestra Project" menu
short_desc: Live Jazz Music

html_data:
Congrats! Aeraco has won Chicago's Best Rock act by the Chicago Music Awards!

Aeraco is America's hard rock band from Chicago, IL. With influences drawn from 80's rock bands mixed with the sound of todays heavy hitters, their style is unmistakably their own. The band has an eclectic writing style and a diverse musical palate. With the mixture of epic rock riffs, a solid rhythm section and powerful vocals, Aeraco sets the bar high. Their music videos have gained them international attention warranting them radio play in the U.K., Italy and the United States. The pairing of guitar virtuosos Matthew "Spidey" Flores and Michael "Ace" Gajewski fuel their songs with a powerful string section. Meanwhile, their bassist Bruce "Beast" Smith and drummer Nick "Misfit" Albaracin lock in to create a pounding rhythmic section sure to elevate your heart rate. Layered on top of a dominant guitar section and cadences any adrenaline junky can march to, the vocals are strong enough to sink anyones sanity into the abyss. Overall, Aeraco provides good old fashioned rock wrapped up in an amazing show that is sure to be one for the history books. The band also has an extensive list of cover songs that is sure to satisfy crowds of all types. The band has played all over the United States including Illinois, Wisconsin, Indiana, Iowa, South Dakota, California, Nevada and more! Aeraco has toured nationally with dates in Chicago, Los Angeles Minnesota, Michigan, South Dakota, Nevada, Wisconsin, Colorado and more,. They're also playing at iconic venues like Hard Rock Cafe Chicago, Whisky A Go-go in Los Angeles, Hard Rock Cafe Las Vegas and Lefty's in Iowa. They have played fests across the country and have provided support for bands like Alice in Chains, Bullet for My Valentine, Breaking Benjamin and more!
short_desc: Aeraco is America's hard rock band from Chicago, IL.

html_data: A tour de force of Chicago musicians, Hood Smoke has been making a lasting impression on listeners all over the world since the release of their debut album LAID UP IN ORDINARY in 2012. Led by bassist and composer Bryan Doherty the band has been recognized as a "must see act" by The Chicago Sun Times. With their second album Regular Neurotic, 2014, the band gained critical notoriety and Doherty was featured in American Songwriter for the song Never Suffering. Vocalo's Live from studio 10 said of Regular Neurotic "Chicago band Hood Smoke is an amalgamation of sounds and genres. Front and center are killer bass grooves and vocals that range from sultry and powerful to piercing and precise. Combine that with atmospheric keys and driving guitars and you have a kind of Soul / Pop fusion that is truly captivating." -- Hood Smoke has played festivals from Summerfest and Jazz in the Park to Logan Boulevard Bash and Taste of Randolph. Theaters and venues throughout the U.S. like Lincoln Hall in Chicago and joint performances with live band power house Umphrey's McGee have kept the band busy touring over the last few years. Their third album Rough Around The Hedges is set to be released in the Spring of 2016. The Hedges showcases what Doherty says to be "our finest work, so far." String trios, brass trios, a small vocal choir, and friends of the band Marquis Hill and Matt Ulery help to make The Hedges one of the highly anticipated releases of 2016.
short_desc: A tour de force of Chicago musicians, Hood Smoke has been making a lasting impression on listeners all over the world since the release of their debut album LAID UP IN ORDINARY in 2012.

name: Larry Carpenter / Santa Claus
html_setlist: Year-round Santa Claus, including Santa's Summer Vacation & Santa Explains it All, a Town Hall Meeting, etc.
html_data: SANTA CLAUS is coming To Town! Santa wants to be a part of the wonderful and exciting events you are planning this summer. Or maybe even help you create a special event you haven't planned . . . until now . . . now that you know he will be in town. “Santa's Summer Vacation” is an activity-packed, interactive, improvisational event. Santa spins stories and tells jokes. He plays games and sings songs with the children. And Santa personally answers questions from children as well as adults. As Santa says, “It's like a town hall meeting, similar to what the politicians do, except I actually answer the questions. And we have a lot more fun.” This is a rare opportunity to meet Santa up close and personal in a much more relaxed atmosphere than during the holidays. While appearing at your venue, Santa greets and interacts with children and their families and poses for pictures in his summer attire. Sometimes, Mrs. Claus joins Santa on vacation! The appearances put the spotlight on the youngsters to create a memorable experience. Santa's appearances can take place anywhere – indoor or outdoor – and require no special technical/theatrical elements to make the event a success. Any place where children and their families gather is the perfect venue! Santa has appeared at malls, theaters, hotels, business establishments, schools and clubs, libraries, public parks and private parties in Chicago, San Diego and Los Angeles. The concept was developed by Larry Carpenter, a professional Santa. He has appeared as Santa at Navy Pier in Chicago and some of the largest malls in America. Through his experiences as Santa, Larry realized that children had wonderful questions and he wanted to find a way to answer them all. “But at Christmas,” Santa says, “I am so busy and the season is so hectic that I barely get to talk to the children. This summer, I hope to meet and talk to children from around the world in a way that I cannot during the holidays. I am looking forward to having lots of fun and bringing joy to all.”
short_desc: Year-round Santa Claus, including Santa's Summer Vacation & Santa Explains it All, a Town Hall Meeting, etc.

html_data: Multi-instrumentalist and singer-songwriter Dwight Ritcher along with BMA Female Vocalist of the Year Nicole Nelson make up the critically acclaimed indie-soul band DWIGHT & NICOLE. Their recent single “I Need Love” was named one of the top 100 Songs of the Year by the Boston Herald and Nelson was coined “The Voice of Vermont” in a cover story printed about her in the Burlington Free Press. She then went on to receive major accolades with her haunting version of Leonard Cohen’s “Hallelujah,” which became a nationwide hit at #24 on the iTunes pop charts. In the summer of 2015, before a pin-drop silent crowd of over 5,000 at Bernie Sanders presidential campaign kick off, Nicole sang a gorgeous rendition of “God Bless America.” It was an unforgettable performance that left the crowd completely stunned. 2015 ended on a very high note with a string of sold out concerts up and down the East Coast; nominations for “Best Vocalist in Vermont,” “Best in State – Vermont,” and “Band of the Year” by the New England Music Awards. In January 2016 DWIGHT & NICOLE spent a magical afternoon at Burlington’s Signal Kitchen with friends & fellow VT act Kat Wright and the Indomitable Soul Band to record a historic version of Woody Guthries “This Land is Your Land”. Their heartfelt rendition has garnered hundreds of thousands of views online over just the first few days, quickly becoming an exciting break out song for the artists involved, and for the Bernie campaign. While the duo is already well known in the Northeast, 2016 finds them poised to break nationally with a new album in the works to be recorded in a secluded studio setting, just outside of Burlington. They will be playing live directly to tape, capturing the unique intimacy, serious chops, and raw power that their fans have come to know and love. DWIGHT & NICOLE are a tight knit band on the brink of major success. Don’t miss a chance to see them live. See what all the talk is about, and go home uplifted and inspired. “Take R&B, soul, blues and jazz, mix in razor-sharp rock guitar (Dwight), a soulful, joyful, foot-stomping, happy-to-be-alive stage energy (Nicole), heat to boiling, and watch your face melt. That’s Dwight & Nicole” ~ Relix Magazine “There are good voices and then there are great voices. Nicole Nelson is definitely the latter.” ~ Christina Aguilera “Magnificent!” ~ Dr. Maya Angelou “Dwight & Nicole are truly great.” ~ Dr. John “Riveting” ~ The Boston Globe
short_desc: Multi-instrumentalist & singer-songwriter Dwight Ritcher along with BMA Female Vocalist of the Year Nicole Nelson make up the critically acclaimed indie-soul band DWIGHT & NICOLE.

html_data: Chicago’s Kelroy create a sound that combines intricacy of composition with simplicity of delivery, drifting between hints of post rock, blues and alternative, as they pour time and essence into the vortex of sound they shape. Each song sets off on a journey of its own. Thick layers of guitars sound more like distress signals and woeful mourning; the keys and trombone add layers of texture and depth, while drums and bass set a pulse that delivers each composition to its natural conclusion. The always-evolving chord progressions, and picturesque and introspective lyrics evoke a mood, a feeling and, undeniably, a train of thought…. Throughout its growth and evolution, the band has been expanding its fan base, having performed in New York, Denver, Cleveland, Columbus, Milwaukee and other cities in the Midwest and on the East Coast. Their music has appeared on public radio like WBEZ and Vocalo, college radio stations like WLUW, and Spanish stations like NOX Live. The band continues to maintain a devoted following in its hometown appearing regularly at such hot-spots as Chicago’s Metro, House of Blues, Lincoln Hall, Martyrs’, Subterranean, Double Door, and many others. Kelroy released their third full-length album in February 2015.
short_desc: Kelroy creates a sound that combines intricacy of composition with simplicity of delivery, drifting between hints of post rock, blues & alternative, as they pour time & essence into the vortex of sound they shape

html_data: Why not have an authentic Chicago Blues Band entertain at your event? International Delmark recording artist Linsey Alexander is available for bookings now! Born in Mississippi and raised in Memphis, Tennessee, Linsey Alexander discovered a down to earth city that truly understands and appreciates music on Chicago's southside. In much the same way as many great blues artists before him, he grew up in a poor but honest and hard working family, learning early on that music has the power to lift the spirit and comfort the soul. In Linsey's own words, "Blues is not hard- it's just a documentary about life." His first guitar - a gift from a family friend who played on the front stoop of Linsey's home in Memphis - was never retrieved from the pawn shop where he left it almost 50 years ago. Using the money to help pay his way to Chicago, he now plays a variety of Gibson and Fender guitars. Since 1959, Linsey Alexander has been perfecting the art of entertainment blues for the sheer and simple pleasure of it. His easy smile and unpretentious personality define a charismatic entertainer who loves to perform; and perform he does! Although having played with B.B.King, Bobby Rush, Buddy Guy, Little Milton, Magic Slim, Johnnie Taylor, A.C.Reed, Larry McCray, Bither Smith, John Primer, Otis Clay, Eddie Clearwater, and other great blues performers, Linsey Alexander has remained resolutely true to his own style. His earlier CD's released, "Someone’s Cookin' in My Kitchen," "My Days Are So Long," and "If You Ain't Got It" are all three compilations of original Blues and R&B tunes. Alexander has been to 10 countries and all across America spreading the joy of blues. He is thankful for the good things in his life, and now at last, seems willing to realize that the friends that encouraged him to keep playing over the years may have known a thing or two about talent. Linsey has "never truly believed in himself" until now; Now, he is ready to believe. In 2012, He signed with Delmark Records and recorded his first international CD, "Been There, Done That." Linsey's recent CD, released in August 2014, "Come Back Baby," landed Linsey a spot as number three best Chicago Blues album. Linsey Alexander was inducted into the Chicago Blues Hall of Fame June 8th, 2014. Linsey Alexander's tour put him in Mexico, Brazil and France. Alexander plans to return to Brazil and France soon in 2016.
short_desc: Why not have an authentic Chicago Blues Band entertain at your even?t! International Delmark recording artist Linsey Alexander is available for bookings now!

html_data: They might be a little bit smaller than your average punk rock band, but The Magnifiers will knock you out. Made up of 10 to 17 year old siblings, The Mags produce a classic sound with a shameless, new-fashioned twist. These four sinling rockers bailed on classical instruments a few years ago to pick up drums and electric guitars and they never looked back. Elliott, the oldest, plays lead guitar and writes the music. Eden sings lead, plays guitar, and writes the band's imaginative lyrics. The Kim Deal of the group is 12 year old bassist and back up singer Eliza. Drummer, Everett, plays louder and faster than you would believe an 10 year old could. He's also known to enjoy MadLibs and sing Fugazi in his sleep. You know, typical 10 year old stuff. Inspired by Operation Ivy, The Aquabats!, Rancid and various YouTube musicians, The Magnifiers set out to write their own music: catchy songs with creative words. Their tunes tend to give a comical and somewhat snarky look at the world and they'll make you highly aware of the probable impending zombie apocalypse. Hopefully you can check them out before then. The Magnifiers.com
short_desc: They might be a little bit smaller than your average punk rock band, but The Magnifiers will knock you out!

html_data: Guns and Ammunition is a Chicago-based five man cover band bringing the fire and fury of "The Only Band That Matters" to the 21st century. Punk, ska, rockabilly, and high energy rock ‘n roll, the timeless music of Joe Strummer and Mick Jones gains new life! Guitarists Tim Burns and Johnny 'Larock' Simpson, drummer Dan Quinn, bassist Dave Martin and singer Shaun Ingram have been bringing The Clash back to Chicago since 2011. From the primal chords of 1978’s Clash City Rockers, to all the anthems -- from classic London Calling (Rolling Stone magazine's #1 album of the 1980s) to the haunting dub of Straight to Hell, from Combat Rock in 1982 to the sounds of the late great Joe Strummer and his Mescaleros and Mick Jones' Big Audio Dynamite -- prepare for a long, faithful journey through the catalog of one of the greatest rock bands!

name: Edward White
html_setlist: 1. Get Toned 2. Work 3. Van Gough
html_data:
Music genres evolve and fluctuate with the decades. And as a genre of music that spawned out of a necessity to spread the story of a people, Hip-Hop has grown and changed as well. It’s evolved and broken into many sub genres over the years. Unfortunately, the sub genre most popularly known by the masses is one that many true Hip-Hop heads passionately dislike. This new popular form of the music is quite often categorized as simply “Commercial Rap”. And just when you think there’s no recovery, a new sub genre and a new voice is born.


YBC Tha Nerd, born Edward White, is an up and coming rapper from the city of Chicago. A member of the group Nerdtastic, formed with friend and partner Black Rambo, YBC Tha Nerd has been rapping for eleven years now. Nerdtastic has been a concept in progress for quite some time, but didn’t actually come to fruition until about a year ago. After hours spent writing and in the studio, with the occasional break for Gaming and Anime, Nerdtastic will certainly be a rap-duo to watch out for.

YBC Tha Nerd was frustrated with the current state of Commercial Rap and wanting to give a voice to those like him, Nerdtastic has created their own sub genre of music which has been dubbed, “Nerd-Hop”. Music for the intelligent, elite and lovers of Hip-Hop is what he promises to deliver. Drawing on inspiration from sources like 2Pac, Common and Mos Def musically and historical philosophers such as Aristotle, Plato and Martin Luther King Jr, this is a genre that promises to astound and enlighten the currently jaded masses. And after years of songs that only create one bad dance after another, Nerdtastic promises to become a great addition to the Hip-Hop legacy. And perhaps offer the salvation, that many might argue, the genre desperately needs.
short_desc: Hip Hop/ EDM/ Dubstep/ Rock

html_data: Chicago based music group Adjacent Cruise was founded in 2015 by Singer-Songwriter Shannon Richardson and Clarinetist/Pianist Yuen Yee Richardson. They combine their different sound, musical styles as well as cultures to create their own unique sound. Adjacent Cruise aims to bring their own differences together as well as collaborate with other musicians and artists from all backgrounds to create something different. Actively performing since July 2016, Adjacent Cruise has performed at Uncommon Ground Chicago, Fitz’s Spare Keys in Elmhurst, Friendly Tap, Gallery Cafe, Goldie’s Chicago, Hip Cat Chicago, ChillFest, Chicago's Irish Christmas Market, Elbo Room, Alibi Bar & Grill in St Charles, etc. as well as some private events. Adjacent Cruise is available to perform as solo, duo, trio or full band at shows, festivals and events from small intimate settings to big outdoor stage in the city of Chicago and nearby suburbs. We perform original music from 30min up to 3-4 hours (optional mix with some cover songs if needed).
short_desc: Adjacent Cruise is a husband and wife duo currently located in Chicago.

html_data: One More Moon is a four-piece from Chicago that got it’s start in early 2015 when singer/songwriter Eric Quigley decided to take his solo work to the next level. Guitarist Roger Smit, bassist Chris Rawlins, and drummer Aaron Schapiro fill out One More Moon’s line up. Their mix of folk, blues, and rock – along with the many differing influences each member brings to the table – transform Quigley’s foundations into songs wholly unique to the band. Since their debut, One More Moon has played various venues in and around Chicago, including the Cubby Bear and the Metro, and a debut EP is in the works.
short_desc: One More Moon is a four-piece band. Their sound is a mix of folk, blues, and rock!

html_data:
A six piece smooth jazz, contemporary jazz band and straight ahead jazz group.

“Sam Hankins is a brilliant trumpeter who stretches himself within the genre of smooth jazz. His tone sometimes hints at Chuck Mangione while his solos are generally more explorative than that of Chris Botti and Rick Braun, even when he caresses melodies. On his latest CD, Nothing Between Us, Hankins plays all of the instruments in most cases, including several brass instruments, keyboards and percussion, taking an effective vocal on the love song “I Can Be.” Throughout the project, Hankins displays the influences of R&B and funky jazz. He has a knack for coming up with memorable and catchy riffs and, like the late Grover Washington Jr, he is capable of playing lengthy solos over fairly simple backgrounds that never lose one’s interest. His ten originals each have their moments. “Nothing Between Us” features some powerful trumpet playing. “See Me” finds Hankins playing muted a la Miles Davis while the ensembles build in density and intensity. One can imagine the rhythmic piece “Reach For Me” being sung someday. “Give It A Try” and “You Should Have” in particularly features Sam Hankins at his best, showing a lot of personality, color and wit in his solos while carving out his own place in contemporary jazz. — Scott Yanow, author of The Jazz Singers, The Great Jazz Guitarists, Jazz On Film and Jazz On Record 1917-76
short_desc: A six piece smooth jazz, contemporary jazz band and straight ahead jazz group.

html_data:
I'm a classically trained guitarist, with a repertoire that spans five centuries and multiple styles. I'm available to play music at all kinds of events such as: concert halls, corporate functions, private parties, weddings, celebrations, religious services, restaurants, ect. I spent a year in Los Angeles studying at Musician's Institute in Hollywood. While in L.A, I studied with Grammy Award winning classical guitarist/composer, Evan Hirschelman. Evan helped me to become a more technically sound, well-rounded, and expressive musician. An injury to the median nerve in my right hand cut my studies short, forcing me to move back to Chicago, where my hand was surgically repaired. Once my hand healed, I continued my studies at Prairie State College and joined the PSC jazz band. I won a most outstanding player award at the Lake County Community College Jazz Contest. I graduated from Prairie State with a Liberal Arts degree and decided to dedicate myself primarily to classical guitar. Upon earning my Associates Degree from PSC, I developed a repertoire of over 30 solo guitar tunes, half of them classical compositions, the other half includes jazz tunes, popular songs, and a few of my own compositions. I've been invited to share my music at multiple weddings and restaurants (Cilantro, Svagatti's, Grape& Grain) in Chicago and its suburbs. Currently, I'm teaching guitar at Down Home Guitars in Frankfort Illinois, and the Beverly Arts Center. In 2013, I decided to continue my classical guitar studies at Columbia College Chicago. I'm a performance scholarship award winner at Columbia College and as of December 2015, I'm a Bachelor of Music graduate.

html_data: For me my work began at the age of 21, but my fascination with DJ-ing started at 17. Growing up in the chicago suburbs, my initial exposure to night life began in my late teens, introducing me to the influential role of the party DJ. I admired the DJ's i experienced and they connected me with the crowd made me want to pursue DJ-ing even more. I learned the basics from a friend and from there began my career. Stepping out into the city club and bar scene in my early 20's, I had met and learned from DJ's around me including Sye Young, DJ Metro, and Rick Garcia. Finding my niche, I learned what I loved to do, "Please the crowd. I am an open format DJ, so I literally can play everything; everything." With musical versatility that is scarcely unmatched, I myself is set apart, but I find most satisfaction in my interaction with the crowd. "To be able to feel everyone's vibe in the room," is what I value most and because of that along with having a great time with what I do, DJ Profess aka me is able to create prolific party experiences for any event at any venue.
short_desc: DJ Profess is able to create prolific party experiences for any event at any venue.

html_data: “International expressionist performance painter Elliott From of Artbeat Live brings a new look and feel to live performance painting.” Elliott From’s performances have been called “explosive”. Whether he is throwing paint at the canvas with frenetic energy, or carefully tracing the outline of an image, there is no mistaking his work. His talent has taken him around the world performing for iconic events such as the Olympic Games, the NHL Playoffs, the Kentucky Derby, and numerous others, but he is most known for his “BIG” heart. To date the sale of Elliott’s work has raised over 3 million dollars for charity, and that number continues to grow. Elliott currently resides in Chicago, and is the owner of Artbeat Live Studios and Artbeat Gallery.
short_desc: “International expressionist performance painter Elliott From of Artbeat Live brings a new look and feel to live performance painting.”

html_data:
WHO IS ADOT NEW SHIT?

Adot New Shit is an indie hip hop/rap artist representing Lifestyle Creative (LCMG). He grew up in the LeClaire Courts projects in Chicago, Illinois. Living around violence and negative surrounding inspired Adot to want more out of life .He has always had a passion for music and was influenced by artists that paved the way like Biggie, Jay Z, Scarface, Fabolous, Kanye West, Lupe Fiasco, Twista, L.E.P., Bump J and Shawnna. These artists aided in molding Adot into the artist that he is today.

Adot has a mission to deliver the best classic rap and hip hop music to the world, and continuously strives to be at the forefront of the music game for decades to come.With his unique lyrical content style, Adot hopes that his music will have an important impact on his audience and will make sure to deliver the best he has to offer.  Adot has performed in different cities opening for other artists such as multi-platinum rapper/producer Soulja Boy.    

 Adot is currently working on releasing new single and also a mixtape entitled “4318 The Sacrifice”, which is set for release during the fall of 2015. You can download the mixtape for free on major hip hop sites and also his website, www.adotnewshit.com.  The lead single from this CD is “9 To 5”  along with the next Single entitled "Ain't Nobody",preparing to release soon, also available on iTunes, Google Play, Spotify. Stay tuned for the release of 4318 The Sacrifice, future tour dates, and more music to come.

html_setlist: All original, have been known to thrown in a cover here and there.
html_data:
Man Fighting Bear is a rock band based in Chicago, IL where two of the three members live.  The other one lives in Hampton, VA.
 
Bill Beach plays piano, organ, synth, and sings backup.
Chris Beach plays drums, percussion, sequencers, and sings backup.
Erik Fagrelius plays bass and sings lead vocal.
 
The band recently released their first full-length recording, Waiting, in 2015.  It was recorded and co-produced by John Ovnik of Deaf Dog Music, and features guest appearances by Ava Cherry (David Bowie, Luther Vandross) and Mark Lekas (Broadway in Chicago, Chicago Symphony Orchestra, Milwaukee Symphony Orchestra.) 
 
All songs are originals and are copyrighted to Man Fighting Bear LLC.  All members of the band are members of ASCAP (Man Fighting Bear LLC).
 
Chris is Bill's son. Erik is Bill's best friend. The band gets along and rarely disagrees. They are notoriously punctual and well dressed.
short_desc: Man Fighting Bear is a Chicago based three piece band playing all original songs.

html_data: ISH provides excellent live music entertainment. As a male/female duo, you get the best of both worlds in a variety of songs! ISH is a Soul/R&B group that performs original music as well as a plethora of cover songs. This group is perfect for parties, weddings, corporate events, and more! ISH performs a variety of songs, and can keep the party live and exciting, or tone it down for background, dinner music. ISH is made up of a husband and wife team. Caleb and Andriea have over 10 years of Classical voice training. The duo has been performing together, since 2007, and their on-stage chemistry is evident in their harmonies. ISH has shared the stage with many reputable artists, including Grammy Award winning singer Faith Evans, the national recording ballad group Enchantment, Tito Jackson, Eric Roberson, Leon Timbo, and Independent Soul Sensation Frank McComb. The group has also been featured on SoulTrain.com among other media publications. The couple has performed on the main stage at The Shrine Chicago, SOB's in New York City, and headlined a nearly sold out concert in Indianapolis at The Jazz Kitchen. The duo’s single “The Vows” was featured in the hit film "Still Standing", which also features Kindred the Family Soul and “Speech” Thomas of Arrested Development. Currently, “The Vows” is in regular rotation on radio shows based in the US, UK, France, Egypt, and Japan. ISH has also been featured on Ebony Magazine’s Power 100 ranked Parenting and Relationships site BlackAndMarriedWithKids.com. In 2014, the duo headlined the inaugural BMWK Marriage Cruise. ISH uses the stage to spread their message of love, marriage, and positivity. Caleb and Andriea believe that live instrumentation is what brings music to life. Creativity is an essential element in their life together, and they feel the need to continue to challenge themselves musically. ISH feels that it is their calling to use their gifts of voice to positively influence and help others.
short_desc: ISH provides excellent live music entertainment. As a male/female duo, you get the best of both worlds in a variety of songs! ISH is a Soul/R&B group that performs original music as well as a plethora of cover songs.

html_setlist: Comedy & hosting for all events.
html_data:
Ronnie Ray, Chicago’s own brings hilarious real life moments to the stage! He found his true passion for comedy at the age of six, thanks to Eddie Murphy and Saturday Night Live. Ronnie began perfecting his craft by listening to his family and the world around him.

The Real Underdog of Comedy, Ronnie Ray a student of comedy. He trained at Second City Chicago, ETA Creative Arts Foundation; Chicago, IL., and Act One Studios; Chicago, IL.. He polished his verbal creativity and ability to write sketches by performing with comedy ensemble OBN “Oui Be Negroes” and Nation of Improv.

Ronnie has been entertaining audiences for years as comic, actor, improviser and voiceover artist.  As a Stand-Up Comedian Ronnie has performed at such Stages as The Improv (Hollywood, Brea, Ontario, Irvine, Miami and West Palm Beach), The Laugh Factory (Hollywood and Chicago), Icehouse Comedy Club (Pasadena,CA) The Famous Comedy Store (Hollywood and La Jolla), Zanies (Chicago and Rosemont) and many other stages across the country. Because of his unique comedy style gave him the opportunity to become the first comedian to perform on Playboy TV and Nickelodeon.

Ronnie Ray did an episode of the television shows, “Grey’s Anatomy”, “Private Practice” and Nickelodeon “Victorious”. He has done an independent film that has been distributed by LIONSGATE “C’mon Man” starring comedians Tony Rock and Rodney Perry. But Ron’s acting career started in 2001 with a role in the Paramount pictures “Save the Last Dance” starring Kerry Washington from ABC Number one Drama “Scandal”. He used his talents for the animated film “Gangs of LA 1991” and worked with Director John Landis on the award winning comedy from “Jib Jab’s Shawshank in a Minute”. But, Ronnie Ray’s passion lies on stage as a comedian knowing the importance of laughter and what it means to people in the world.

INFLUENCES: Richard Pryor, Eddie Murphy, Bill Cosby, Redd Foxx, Rodney Dangerfield, George Carlin and Moms Mabely.

Ronnie Ray is available for up and coming shows.
short_desc: Stand-Up Comedian, writer, actor and Event Host.

html_data: Born into a family of musicians, singers and songwriters, Charlie's unquenchable passion for great music and melodies seemed only natural.  He grew up listening to Earth Wind and Fire, Stevie Wonder, and The Doobie Brothers among other greats, so it’s no surprise that by the age of 6 he was singing and performing with his siblings for family and friends.  It wasn't until high school though that he really got the bug, and flourished.  This is when he picked up the guitar and never looked back, playing solo gigs 3-4 times a week and consistently writing his own music.   Recent artist influences such as Gavin DeGraw, Ed Sheeran, Andy Grammer and John Mayer inspired Charlie to concentrate on songwriting, and ultimately his first EP.  His father, Bill, a producer, writer and musician who reached the billboard charts in the 80’s, produced Charlie’s 4 song self-titled debut.  The sounds of the EP are a punchy combination of 2016 Pop and Soul, Hip Hop, Gospel, EDM, and Classic Singer/Songwriter. In 2013 and 2014 Charlie was contacted by the producers of  “The Voice” and invited to audition in both Chicago and Dallas.  His arresting single “Take Control” recently reached #7 on Internet Radio Station Q108 Kingston.
short_desc: Independent Pop Singer/Songwriter, Recording Artist and Vocalist.

html_data: Winner of the 2015 MAMA award for best cover band, Steely Dane is dedicated to not only faithfully reproducing the Steely Dan and Donald Fagen songbook, but to bringing an energetic live-show experience to the crowd. 20 of Madison, WI's (located in "Dane" County) best jazz and rock musicians have banded together around their passion for Steely Dan music, playing in the same configuration as the Steely Dan touring band including a four piece horn section and three background singers. html_data: By going back to the roots of American Music and adding their own gritty and powerful interpretation to North Mississippi Hill Country Blues, Americana, New Orleans Classics, Folk and Gospel, The Marshall County Trio takes the audience on a historical musical journey.  From The Marshall County Trio's own original compositions, to the early blues songs of Mississippi Fred McDowell, Fury Lewis and Hambone Willie Newbern, through the more recent influences of R.L. Burnside, Ryan Bingham, HoneyHoney, Johnny Cash, Robert Earl Keen and The North Mississippi Allstars, the listener is transported across a wide breadth of musical genres, all with the unique arrangement and interpretation of The Marshall County Trio.
short_desc: Country Blues, Americana, New Orleans Classics, Folk and Gospel, The Marshall County Trio takes the audience on a historical musical journey.

html_data: World Class champion Elvis Tribute Artist and voice over artist. Known worldwide as "The TRUE Voice of Elvis" by not only his fans and peers, but by those who knew Elvis personally, Doug Church is regarded as an Icon in the industry. Doug began his tribute career while in the US Air force winning 11 First Place trophies in the annual Air Force talent contests. He worked with the Las Vegas tribute Show "Legends in Concert" for 7 years, then developed and produced his own show "Doug Church, The TRUE Voice of Elvis" which tours the US and the world. He has performed in such sundry locations as Bermuda, the Bahamas, Jamaica, England, Germany, Denmark, Moscow, Finland, Sweden, Chile, Spain, Norway, Wales, and Canada. Doug's voice has been widely acknowledged, by his fans and peers, as being the closest to Elvis, and he provided the background vocals in the Award Winning documentary film "Almost Elvis". In 2000 he was the voice behind the widely acclaimed CD project "Kingtinued", a collection of modern-day hits sung in the style of Elvis Presley. In 2004 he was chosen as the spokesperson by the Hershey Corporation to promote the "Reese's Elvis Peanut Butter and Banana Cup" and toured the country as their premier ETA. He wrote and starred in a "how to" series of videos called "Sing Like the King", produced by Blue Suede Films. Doug has recently had the honor of being selected by RLF Victor Productions as one of two singers, from amongst hundreds of talented artists, to reproduce the sound of Elvis Presley for the new feature film Fame & Fortune, the story of Memphis Mafia member and Elvis Presley bodyguard Sonny West's incredible seventeen year friendship and life journey with Elvis Presley, whose theatrical release is coming soon...
short_desc: World Class champion Elvis Tribute Artist and voice over artist

html_data: If your goal is to hear the freshest sounds Chicago has ever encountered, look no further than The Mashed Potatoes. For over 6 years, The Mashed Potatoes have dedicated themselves to mastering a funky sound that expands over several decades of music. We pride ourselves on accommodating any song request we receive from our clients as our #1 goal is to make your event the best it can be. The Mashed Potatoes, much like the food they're named after, are malleable to fit whatever your needs are. At our largest, the band consists of 8 talented musicians and vocalists, which is perfect if you're looking for an impressive sound for parties, private/corporate events, weddings, etc. The Mashed Potatoes can also easily break down to as small as a duo, if you're looking for something more intimate. In the simplest of terms, The Mashed Potatoes will work hard towards your happiness!
short_desc: If your goal is to hear the freshest sounds Chicago has ever encountered, look no further than The Mashed Potatoes!

html_data: Born in Elgin,IL, Bruno Zuniga has always been energetic on and off the stage, creating an experience for fans that will have them dancing in the car at 3:00 AM after his shows. Being only 17, Bruno has received the experience to play at nightclubs around the Chicagoland area such as Zero Gravity and the legendary Medusas Nightclub on multiple occasions. With his first public release mix on SoundCloud, Bruno received 4,000+ plays. Along with his DJing success Bruno has also received Instagram support on his anonymous alias from multiple artists such as Slushii, Sikdope, and Herobust to name a few.

html_data: Los Perros Cubanos features the music of Cuba’s Golden Age of the 1940s and 1950s. Since its inception in 2009, Los Perros Cubanos has become one of the Midwest’s hottest Latin acts. The band’s music combines the traditional Cuban music styles of Son Cubano, Salsa, Cha Cha, and Charanga with modern instrumental prowess to produce a captivating sound that moves your feet. Los Perros Cubanos take the influences of such Latin music immortals as Buena Vista Social Club, Beny Moré, Arsenio Rodriguez, Celia Cruz, Tito Puente, and Compay Segundo, and blend jazz, blues, rock and country into the mix to create a totally unique sound. You’ve never heard anything like Los Perros Cubanos! Prepare to dance the night away!
short_desc: Los Perros Cubanos features the music of Cuba’s Golden Age of the 1940s and 1950s. Since its inception in 2009, Los Perros Cubanos has become one of the Midwest’s hottest Latin acts.

name: The Lori Brittin Group
html_data: Lori Brittin, accomplished Chicago jazz/pop singer, and her team of world class musicians will bring sophistication and elegance to your event. For over 20 years Lori and her musicians have provided entertainment for hundreds of events in Chicago which include corporate functions, galas, weddings, outdoor festivals, opening acts for major stars and private functions for some of Chicago’s Elite Families. Lori’s repertoire includes songs from the Great American Song Book as well as popular songs from the 50’s to the present, performed in her own inimitable, jazzy style.

name: Swingabilly Slim and the Slim-Tones
html_data: Swingabilly Slim and the Slim-Tones is the answer to all of your musical questions.  We play an intriguing blend of swingabilly music that combines the best traits of the sophisticated jump swing of the 1930s and 1940s and the energetic rockabilly rhythyms of the late 1950s and early 1960s, as well as the plentiful au courant throwbacks to those magnificent eras.  The mix appeals to a broad swath of listeners, from twenty-something hipsters looking for something new (yet old) to groove to while sipping a locally sourced vegan espresso or a lukewarm PBR and tapping their Doc Martens to the latest beat, all the way to splendiforous seniors rocking their way into their golden years while tapping their Dr. Scholls to the swinging sounds of yesteryear. And everything in between.  We are all things to all people...as long as your thing is swing!
short_desc: Swingabilly Slim is a Chicago based swing, rock, rockabilly, swingabilly and jazz band playing restaurants, bars, clubs and private events.
