html_data: The Shades are a trio of Chicago's top singer-songwriters: NBC The Voice's Andrew DeMuro, & brothers Phil & Mark Jacobson. Equipped primarily with their voices and acoustic guitars, The Shades possess a signature sound that encompasses elements of popular music from folk & rock, to soul & R&B. Impressive arrangements and tight harmonies are the hallmarks of The Shades’ original music, and critics across generations have taken notice. In 2015, their original song, ‘Take You Home,’ was featured in American Songwriter Magazine as a ‘Daily Discovery,’ and was chosen as a finalist in NewSong Music’s International Songwriting Competition. The group received further honors in 2016 when Andrew was selected as a member of Adam Levine's team on Season 11 of NBC's The Voice. Having graced a variety of Chicago’s stages, including House of Blues, Evanston SPACE, Mayne Stage & Navy Pier, The Shades have spent much of 2016 in the recording studio working on an upcoming EP release. Keep up with The Shades on social media (@WeTheShades).
short_desc: The Shades are a trio of Chicago's top singer-songwriters: NBC The Voice's Andrew DeMuro, & brothers Phil & Mark Jacobson.

html_data:
Chicago's Premier 90's to Now Party Rock Cover Band!

Started in 2015, Winnie Cooper is a collection of former touring musicians focused on delivering high-energy shows featuring the greatest rock music from the 90's to today.
Hailing from the northern Chicago suburbs, Winnie Cooper focuses on the full Chicagoland area, extending from Kenosha to Joliet.

The music

Winnie Cooper was born from a love of music, featuring songs from the Foo Fighters, Fall Out Boy, No Doubt, My Chemical Romance, Maroon 5, Paramore, Weezer, The Pretty Reckless, Stone Temple Pilots, Wolfmother, Incubus, Veruca Salt, Nirvana, Queens of the Stone Age, Panic! At The Disco, Filter, The Strokes, Green Day, Muse, Red Hot Chili Peppers, Good Charlotte, Jane's Addiction, Jimmy Eat World, The All-American Rejects, The Toadies, The Donnas, Wheatus, Harvey Danger, and many, many more.

Events

Winnie Cooper is available to play traditional venues, Festivals, Corporate Events, Weddings, and parties of any kind!
short_desc: 90's to Now Party Rock Cover Band!

html_setlist: Daniel has en enormous repertoire ranging from jazz standards of the 50's to classic hits. Daniel is comfortable providing both solo and band arrangements for any music ranging from jazz, latin, soul, blues, reggae, funk, disco, pop and RnB. A typical hour long set list for a festival would be something like the following 1. AInt no Sunshine 2. Get Lucky 3. Isnt She Lovely 4. Folsom Prison 5. You are my sunshine 6. Get by with a little help 7. Wind Cries Mary 8. Gravity 9. What a wonderful world 10. How sweet it is ( to be loved by you ) These are just a few examples of songs that Daniel loves to perform either solo or with a group.
html_data: Since 2014 Daniel Cronson has been building a name for himself as an original and inspired blues and soul artist. Daniel makes a living playing daily in restaurants as well as hosting clubs at night. Daniel also sources additional work performing at weddings, parties, fundraisers and many other events. His music ranges from classic artists such as Stevie Wonder and Sam Cooke, to current artists such as Bruno Mars or Sam Smith. During the summer Daniel can often be found street performing along Michigan avenue and Millenium Park as well as playing in clubs or hosting open mics throughout the city at night. Daniel also produces and performs his own original music as well. Daniel specializes in many different ways of presenting his music from playing in full nine piece bands, or leading a trio, to doing solo sets with a looping pedal. For superb musicianship with a great attitude and work ethic, contact Daniel Cronson for all of your live music needs.

html_data:
Starting in July of 2000 the founding members of Kist set out to launch a band worthy of the moniker “a tribute to Kiss.”
   The time is now and that initial vision has arrived. After years of diligence, including a nation-wide talent search, Kist has attained it’s initial goal and continues to strive for a show that keeps the fans asking for more.
    Basing it’s stage show on the unrivaled Kiss shows of the 1970’s, Kist derives it’s set-list mostly from the make-up era catalogue, but does add in a few "out of make-up catalouge suprises.
    Visually, the band prides itself on members that physically “fit” the part.
    Sonically, countless hours of study and rehearsal has helped hone the band’s razor sharp edge. A Kist show brings all the fire and magic one would expect at a Kiss show.
     Booking KIST along with proper promo ensures a "slam dunk" for your venue or event because their goal is to deliver the goods with every performance from load-in thru set-up, performance and after show meet 'n' greets.
short_desc: KISS tribute band

html_data: Chix Pix and Stix has been making an extraordinary name for themselves across the Midwest and are very quickly becoming a leading cover band in their home state, Illinois. Unlike many of their friends in the cover market, Chix Pix and Stix offers a new edge to the cover band world with unmatched versatility that spans over multiple genres including Pop, Motown, Country, Metal, Soul, R&B, Disco, and Rock n’ Roll. Chix Pix and Stix can preform anywhere from 30 min - 5 hours. With two tremendous voices of Chicago’s well-known female lead singers, this unforgettable band covers both billboard charted and fan favorite songs from the 60’s all the way to 2000’s making them an instant hit everywhere they play. What truly makes this band stand out from other popular cover bands is the unique way Chix Pix and Stix tailors every show by working closely with each venue to discover that venue’s specific style and customer demographic which they use to create set list choices. Throughout the show the tailoring continues as Chix Pixand Stix reads the crowds allowing the crowd flow inspire all final and additional song selections. Their talent mixed with their ability to arouse and encourage crowd participation is unparalleled. Chix Pix and Stix is the ultimate cover band for any occasion. Whether a venue is looking to create a remarkable experience for their guests or a wedding/corporate event is in need of live entertainment to keep people smiling and having a great time, Chix Pix and Stix is always the best choice. We also have the option of a remarkable Acoustic Duo with our extremely talented Lead Guitarist and Lead singer for venues that do not have the space for a full band or who are looking for an awesome addition to their patio during the summer.
short_desc: Chix Pix and Stix has been making an extraordinary name for themselves across the Midwest and are very quickly becoming a leading cover band in their home state, Illinois.

html_data: The Sofia Goodman Group is a jazz funk group led by drummer Sofia Goodman. She has been called brilliant (Ace Records) and the band has been credited as a 'fascinating and fun' (Cailey Lindberg, music journalist). The Sofia Goodman Group was born in the mind of drummer Sofia Goodman in 2012, when she was living in Boston after graduating Berklee College of Music. Sofia was highly influenced by Esperanza Spalding, the grammy award winning jazz artist, whom she performed with at Berklee.
short_desc: The Sofia Goodman Group is a jazz funk group led by drummer Sofia Goodman.

html_data:
Allan Craig has been touring for many years, and has been blessed to visit so many great places, experience so many new things, and meet so many amazing people. “My love and passion for music has carried me thus far through a career I am proud of - I’ve toured with national headliners, I’ve played in several famous venues, and I’ve swelled with pride when a crowd sings my songs back to me.  I also feel the same passion when I get in front of a small crowd, that personal connection is amazing!’  Allan has taken his music to the international market place with two hit songs reaching the top of the European Country Music Charts.  “Its amazing to have fans all over the world!  I never thought that would happen!  That is not something you plan on!”   As an artist Allan is hungry, looking for the next step to take. “Music is such a huge part of my life, and as long as I get to keep sharing it, and keep growing, I’ll be fulfilled.” Allan brings a vibe and flare of many decades of music to his live shows.  Music you can dance to, sing along with, and music that makes an audience feel something special. “I take pride in being entertainer, no matter what venue I may be in, Im always aiming to leave the crowd anxious for more, I'm always anxious for the crowd giving me more!  Its an awesome experience between the two of us!!”  

Allan Craig, has shared the stage with National acts such as Florida Georgia Line, Luke Bryan, Zac Brown Band, and more. He has toured over 40 states and performed in some of the country’s most notorious venues. As Allan continues to grow in his career, the sky truly is the limit. His music is that American Country style fans know and love, with catchy melodies and lyrics that anyone can appreciate. Anyone who’s seen Allan live can attest to the fun and excitement that comes with one of his shows, with an endless supply of energy and clear passion for music that shines through in every single song.
short_desc: Allan Craig - American Music Artist

name: Cels Dupri
html_data: Cels Dupri is a Conscious Lyricist from the south side of Chicago. He first fell in love with Hip Hop at the early age of eight when exposed to artist such as LL Cool J, Nas and many more. Soon after, he started writing poetry which lead to his deep love for writing. Although he’s been writing and recording since his early days it was only in June of 2016 when Cels decided to take his music career serious and pursue it full time. Since June he put out his first and second projects entitled “AMBITIONZ” and “TRIUMPH” and is currently in the works his third project. Some of his accolades thus far is touring around the US (Atlanta, Austin, Boston, Cleveland, ETC), being invited to perform at multiple festivals like Auburn Street Festival and A3C, also being able to have his music reach over five thousand plus listeners.

html_data: Few Miles On is a self-described Southern Blues Groove band made up of veteran musicians with different backgrounds from Detroit, Chicago and Nashville with one thing in common: they all grew up playing music and all are from blue collar, working class families. Drawing from that shared life experience they found a recipe to blend it into a musical style like no other band. Two words: Power Trio. Their original compositions employ a wide range of rhythmic grooves and styles, soulful vocals, and memorable guitar lines and on occasion the added texture of a Hammond organ. Listening to a Few Miles On album takes you right back to the early 70’s; a golden era of creative freedom when many of their musical influences dominated the radio airwaves. On stage they understand how to connect with their audience and bring them along as the band moves through a set filled with rocking shuffles, emotional ballads, funky grooves and hypnotic delta blues numbers. At their live performances fans often say it is hard to believe that a three-piece band could create such a big sound. Catch one of their sets and discover Few Miles On for yourself!
short_desc: Few Miles On is a self-described Southern Blues Groove band made up of veteran musicians with different backgrounds from Detroit, Chicago and Nashville with one thing in common: they all grew up playing music and all are from blue collar, working class families.

html_data: Bringing the Summer Sun year-round in Chicago. *JBTV performance aired March 8, 2017 w/ The Orwells, NE-HI & Circa Waves *1st full length album, "Tides", released August 2016 *Several sold old performances in 2016: Lincoln Hall, Subterranean, Double Door, Beat Kitchen, etc. *Performed at the Remix Festival *South Africa Fall tour in 2017 It all started in Chicago and somehow ended up in sunny Berlin. Chicago-based Ballroom Boxer was looking to work with someone on their first single and subsequent album. After a few warm leads with a couple of L.A. producers, they finally found a fit in Gordon Raphael, their hero for his work on the first couple of Strokes’ albums, as well as Electrical Audio, recently featured on Dave Grohl’s/Foo Fighters HBO special ‘Sonic Highways’. “We wanted to forge our own path on our first album so we rethought everything,” singer/guitarist, Mike Altier said. “We skipped (working with) a label and instead, used the money from commercial licensing to write the album at a Wisconsin lakehouse, work on the first single with Gordon via Berlin and track the rest of the album at Electrical Audio with Jon San Paulo and Flashpoint Tribeca with Tim Rusin.” So far the way they’ve re-imagined the recording process is paying off. The band has already generated interest from labels, radio stations and festivals, including playing in South Africa in 2017. The band created a Snapchat lyric video for their first single, ‘Make It Home’ engineered by Gordon Raphael. The new album, 'Tides', is available everywhere digitally and on vinyl at https://ballroomboxer.bandcamp.com/album/tides-2. Give it a wiggle!
short_desc: Summer rock n roll band from Chicago.

name: Addy's Corner
html_setlist: Sample: All The Small Things - Blink-182 Inside Out - Eve 6 Sugar, We're Going Down - Fall Out Boy Everlong - Foo Fighters Hey Jealousy - Gin Blossoms Sweetness - Jimmy Eat World Hanging By A Moment - Lifehouse I Write Sins, Not Tragedies - Panic! At The Disco All Star - Smash Mouth Otherside - Red Hot Chili Peppers Say It Ain’t So - Weezer More songs found here: http://addyscorner.com/setlist/
html_data:
Addy's Corner want to change what you think a cover band can be.

“We grew up going to see the bands we cover, and those shows were loud and heavy and the crowd is moving and singing along,” says vocalist Brian Rowe. “You're part of a community, so you drop your inhibitions and become a part of the night, both in the audience and on the stage. I don't get the same feeling from cover bands. So with our band, we wanted to bring the experience of seeing all your favorite bands in the same night, and give the audience the same feeling of community and enthusiasm, to have a unique experience among cover bands.”

Based out of Chicago, Addy's Corner plays your favorite songs from your high school years. Focusing on alternative and pop punk from the 90's and 2000's, their shows promote maximum crowd participation and monumental sing-alongs for the entire night. There are no outfits, no gimmicks- just raw energy.

 The band derives their setlist from days spent listening to Chicago’s Q101, hearing artists like Red Hot Chili Peppers and Foo Fighters played in heavy rotation, but also lesser known hits of the early 2000’s by Fall Out Boy, Yellowcard, and Panic! At The Disco. The band also puts their own spin on some well known hits, such as their fist-pumping cover of Smash Mouth’s All Star.

Founded in 2015, the band has played all over Chicago, including headlining slots at House of Blues, The Original Mothers, and rounding out 2016 at Cubby Bear. They have also played Durty Nellies in Palatine, Blarney Island in Antioch, Adobe Gilas in Rosemont and Chicago, and Uptown Lounge in Chicago. The band can entertain crowds for a full night and also put on special event shows for any audience.

 Addy’s Corner is looking ahead to 2017, where they plan to continue playing Chicago venues and branch out to bring their specific brand of rock covers to new audiences.

html_data:
Royal Outsiders (previously The Central Standard) is an alternative indie rock band from Chicago, IL.  After meeting in college, founders Steven Phillips (lead guitar) Alex Garrison (lead vocalist) began jamming in small campus apartments off and on for several years.  Soon after graduating, the duo began  collaborating on new original material in a Illinois suburban basement.  After an introduction from a coworker, the two met with acclaimed producer Sean O'Keefe and began discussing recording a self-funded EP.  A month later the duo completed production on their debut EP and quickly added new members Mike Bronk (bass), Manny Miller (rhythm guitar) and Jack McKee (drums) to complete the outfit.

Under the name Royal Outsiders, the band has began writing new material in the same basement the original duo began their first material.  Influenced by an eclectic mix of genres ranging from southern inspired rock and blues to modern indie rock, the band has continued to hone in on its sound with the goal to record a full length album in the near future.  Armed with new material, the band has begun to make waves in the Chicago music scene with aspirations of making its footprint known on a national basis.
short_desc: Indie Rock Band

Song list of originals includes: How Bad, Whatever It Takes, Jesus Can Heal the Pain, I'm In Love With the One Above, Come See About Me, I Saw A Miracle, Heavenly Filled, Deeper Still, Get Me Through the Night, I Shall Never Forget, Stop and Look Around, Heaven Knows Me
html_data: Our band delivers musical performance of primarily original songs that blend gospel, blues, rock, and soul music. We are comfortable in a variety of settings, such as in clubs, festivals, community events and parties, and church services or church-related special events. The Annie Young Gospel Blues Band is a new musical group based in Elgin, IL. The band is Annie Young on vocals, Greg Schiller on bass, Bill Crampton on harmonica, Bruce Scoville on drums, and Joe Misek on electric guitar. Since she was a young girl, Annie Young wanted to be a singer. Throughout her life, she sang in choirs at church, and wrote lyrics to potential songs, saving them for over twenty years in some cases. Without any musical education, Annie waited patiently for musicians to come into her life and bring her songs to life. At the Vineyard Church of Elgin, Annie collaborated with several musicians to compose and record her first song, I Saw A Miracle. The church issued a CD of original music from members of the church, and I Saw A Miracle landed on it and quickly became a favorite of the church. Several years later, Annie met Bill Crampton, a multi-instrumentalist who loved the idea of lending his harmonica playing to Annie's blues and gospel music. Then Annie met Joe Misek, an electric guitar player and blues enthusiast. The three met to jam, and new songs started to emerge. The first two songs the trio wrote, Come See About Me and Jesus Can Heal the Pain became staples in their repertoire whenever they shared their music with people. More songs emerged, and eventually the group decided to record a full, ten song CD in the summer of 2014. The resulting CD is Jesus Can Heal the Pain, Annie's debut CD. After six months of occasionally playing as a trio for small crowds, the group decided to assemble a full electric band. Greg Schiller, who played bass on the CD, rejoined the fray in the fall of 2015, and Bruce Scoville joined as their drummer in the summer of 2016. Together, the Annie Young Gospel Blues Band blends styles that historically fuse the expression of pain and the expression of joy. Both blues and gospel music heal and celebrate. Behind each original song in the band's catalog is a story from Annie's life. If you can somehow manage to suppress your dancing and clapping enough to listen deeply to the story, you see that the songs do not airbrush out the rough parts of the narrative. Rather, the songs celebrate the victory over life's troubles, the faith in God that brought Annie through, and the hope we have that we can endure the next trial that comes. In a recent talent competition, Annie and each instrumentalist backing her up were each described as a "powerhouse". Whether you hear their music live or recorded in the studio, you will be inspired and full of joy by the Annie Young Gospel Blues Band.
short_desc: Our band delivers musical performance of primarily original songs that blend gospel, blues, rock, and soul music.

Fall Back to You - Perpetual Process from Niche Visuals - Ralph Klisiewicz on Vimeo.
html_data: Perpetual Process started as a simple musical experimentation. Over a decade, however, this experimentation grew into an eclectic blend of lush female vocals, exotic electronic sounds, and mix of live instruments. The project was founded by Ralph Klisiewicz, who writes and produces most of the content. The initial idea was to produce mostly electronic music. At the time inception of Perpetual Process, the computer plug-in revolution was taking place. This made the production of music possible without the need of a commercial studio. The decision was made to avoid electronic DJ like sets and instead perform Perpetual Process music in a setting of live instruments. Therefore, Ralph set out to form a band. First member to join Perpetual Process was Cornelius Boon. Cornelius is a bass player with many years of live experience. Cornelius moved to Chicago in 1995 and joined industrial band 13MG. The band toured nationally for 4 years. He also played a series of shows with the Final Cut, including opening dates with Pigface. Given his experience, he has been essential in the transition of Perpetual Process from an electronic home studio project to a live band. Perpetual Process rotated several singers and drummers while performing at local Chicago venues for few years. Eventually the band settled on Kevin (Jrumz) Jones who is a studio drummer working in Chicago. He developed his skills initially playing for various gospel bands. However, over the last several years he has been hired to record for artists ranging in various styles such as rock, R&B and Funk. One could say that his style is a fusion of Stewart Copeland and Carter Beauford. The addition of such a talented drummer immediately added an organic element to the Perpetual Process sound while maintaining its roots to electronics. Katie Somers was the last musical piece added to Perpetual Process. Katie has been studying music for years. She also helped run a children's music school in Chicago’s north suburbs. Katie has a smooth jazzy-lounge style yet her voice posses a powerful emotional drive. Her voice is now an instantly recognizable component of what makes the unique sound of Perpetual Process.
short_desc: Perpetual Process started as a simple musical experimentation. Over a decade, however, this experimentation grew into an eclectic blend of lush female vocals, exotic electronic sounds & mix of live instruments.

name: Gary West "For the love of Cash"
html_setlist: A wide variety of Cash favorites as well as classics from Waylon, Willie, Haggard and country music legends as well as originals featured on his latest album, "For the love of Cash, Volume 2", released in September 2016.
html_data: With nearly 30 years of experience working beside many of the legends of country music including Tommy Cash, Little Jimmy Dickens, Del Reeves, and other Opry greats, Gary West has a unique perspective and a strong reverence for the timeless music he grew up with. In addition to his many years performing on the world famous Grand Ole Opry, he has also toured extensively throughout the US, Canada, and Europe. West has developed a remarkable show which is a tribute to Johnny Cash and the legends of country music, including , remembering Merle Haggard, Waylon Jennings. With his uncanny ability to channel not only the spirit but also the sound of these legends, West brings their music alive on stage every night with some of his own versions and amazing impromptu impersonations of Ray Charles, John Conlee, to Hank Hill and Edith Bunker. You never know what is to come, but you can bet it will be fun and entertaining. His audience is full of an interesting mix of longtime classic country fans and a whole new generation, who are excited to discover this enduring music for the first time.

name: BLCK Parliament
html_data: Black Parliament (stylized as BLCK or BL^CK Parliament) is an American hip hop collective formed in 2016, in Chicago, Illinois, by members Sonny BLCK, iBmadeit and J.Paul. BLCK Parliament is a collective of rappers, record producers, music video directors and Industry Professionals, who share similar interests in music, fashion, style and art. The collective mainly consists of Chicago-based rappers, most of whom have been active in Chicago Hip Hop Scene since 2003-2006. The collective's resident record producer, iBmadeit, has produced for or worked with several Chicago, Los Angeles & New York based Artists, most notably Big O Mr290, Hypno Carlito, Crucial Conflict, Do Or Die, Cypress Hill, Cuban Link & Taylor Gang. Group members Sonny BLCK & J.Paul has also managed to garner pretty respectable followings for themselves as solo artists or members of other groups. Sonny BLCK also functions as the collective’s de-facto business and brand specialist, having also worked as a successful event promoter and entertainment consultant for local artists since 2010. The group is currently gearing up to release iB's full featured LP titled "Tears Of Gold", set to be released in Summer 2017. The collective also plans to release a BLCK Parliament group project in Fall 2017.
short_desc: Black Parliament (stylized as BLCK or BL^CK Parliament) is an American hip hop collective

name: The Master Mind--Brent Webb
html_data:
Brent Webb will astound you! It's just that simple. He will amaze you and make you laugh. Using what he calls 'heightened sensory perception', he will know what's on your mind before you do. He will predict with uncanny accuracy your actions before you make them. 

He sees with your eyes.... 
He hears with your ears..... 
He thinks with YOUR mind! 

He will predict your actions and thoughts with uncanny accuracy, from the name of your first love to the amount of change in your pocket. He performs a high speed, interactive, stage extravaganza that will have you questioning what is real and unreal. Webb's show is a breathtaking, dramatic, and energetic voyage to the farthest reaches of your mind! 

He captures the imaginations of audiences everywhere with his energetic and refreshingly innovative presentations. Audience participation, side splitting comedy, and a magnetic display of showmanship are all creatively combined into a performance you will remember. 

Webb's performance is an extraordinary blend of mystery, humor, psychology, and intuition. Brent dazzles the mind as he challenges his audiences to question what is real and what is unreal; what is possible and what is impossible. 

Brent has performed his fast paced show around the globe, from Miami to Brazil and The Bahamas to Spain, one thing is certain, his show is one your guests or employees will remember forever! 

Brent Webb engages the entire audience, making each and every one of them a part of the show. The beauty of Brent's program is his ability to play to any size group, from five to five thousand, the impossible and unbelievable happens in front of your very eyes, in fact.... 
seeing is.. DISBELIEVING!

name: Crystal Day
html_setlist: Prom Night in Pontiac 2. Wings of Fire 3. You Won’t Leave Me Alone 4. Dodged a Bullet 5. Dock of the Bay/Proud Mary Medley (COVER) 6. Everything in It 7. Shine on You 8. Can't Feel My Face (COVER) 9. California 10. Can't Stop the Feeling (COVER) 11. I Like It Like That 12. Karma Like Flowers
html_data:
It is said that home is where the heart is. For Virginian Crystal Day, the spotlight is where she calls home. Her powerhouse vocals and prodigious writing ability lends her a musical style comparable to that of Shania Twain and Katy Perry. There is no denying that she is comfortable with sharing her gift to a crowd. 

As the daughter of a racetrack owner, Crystal was accustomed to being in front of large audiences beginning at a very young age. On her eighth birthday, she was serenated by a crowd of 100,000 at Charlotte Motor Speedway and a few short years later, she was there performing the National Anthem for the same crowd. The young songstress released a debut album, Anything Can Happen, at the age of thirteen. This lead to opportunities to sing the National Anthem at NASCAR’s Martinsville (Virginia), South Boston Motor Speedway (Virginia) and at Orange County Speedway (North Carolina). 

Her passion, hard work and immense talent earned her an opening slot for multi-platinum recording artist Martina McBride. These performances lit a fire in Crystal that could not be put out. The South Boston, VA native’s passion eventually led her to Los Angeles to perform at Universal Studios for the World Championships of Performing Arts where she placed gold against top singers from around the world. In addition, she became the youngest American to be invited to perform in the Amsterdam Music Festival. Here she had the opportunity to perform in front of 30,000 people daily. Her success in Amsterdam led her to begin touring the Eastern Hemisphere where she gained fans from Spain to China. “It completely changed my life, in the best way possible. My eyes were open to a world much bigger than I ever imagined.”

Despite her powerful vocals and remarkable songwriting ability, she adds yet something else to her resume. She is an accomplished actress. Her love of theatre started at the age of six. Her largest adolescent role came when she was eight when she starred as Marta Von Trapp (second youngest child) in the popular musical, The Sound of Music. The production was performed eight times a week and her father was adamant that he attended every performance. “Within just a few performances, my Dad knew every line throughout the musical. He was the first one to know whenever anyone messed up” laughed Crystal.  After high school, Crystal packed her bags and moved to Los Angeles and landed a leading role in the movie The Passing, where she co-starred alongside Paul Gleason (The Breakfast Club, Die Hard). In addition, she was a part of the theatre production of Tobacco Road, performing alongside Lin Shaye (There’s Something About Mary, Insidious). She has also starred in several Verizon and Apple commercials, the Young and the Restless, Snow White, Grease and a few films that are set to be released in 2016. 

With a passion to act and perform, Crystal’s main motivation is to be an entertainer. “I can’t image doing anything else in my life.” She re-directed her focus back on music and teamed up with Grammy-winning producer Tom Weir at Studio City Sound (Kelly Clarkson, Lee Ann Womack, Willie Nelson, LMFAO). During that time, she also began taking classes at the Songwriting School of Los Angeles. After honing her songwriting craft in L.A., Crystal took her talents to Music City where she began co-writing with top-notch songwriters, joining forces with famed Nashville producer Biff Watson (Blake Shelton, Keith Urban, Tim McGraw, Lady Antebellum, Charles Kelley, Martina McBride, etc.) and developing material for her upcoming EP Brave, which contains five powerful songs that showcase her stunning writing ability and flawless vocals. 

This effervescent gal has managed to check multiple things off her list. With musical influences including The Beatles, Garth Brooks, Shania Twain and Katy Perry, her biggest female role model is Oscar-winning actress Julie Andrews (The Sound of Music, Mary Poppins, etc). “I was at a wedding with her and I admit, I was fangirling. Your expectations are so high when you meet someone you’ve looked up to your whole life and she was everything I wanted her to be. She carries herself so classy. Definitely something I will always remember!” 

Day’s talents don’t stop at performing; the tunesmith is also an accomplished author. Having always turned to writing during tough times, she was inspired to write her first children’s book after a tragic family event. The book has since developed into a series. With her unyielding confidence and a go get ‘em attitude, Crystal has set the bar high and if her stage presence and immense talent are any indicator of what’s to come, the finish line is nowhere in sight.
short_desc: Powerhouse vocals & prodigious writing ability lends her a musical style comparable to that of Shania Twain & Katy Perry.

name: Thrift Store Halo
html_data:
American Indie Alt-Power-Pop-Rock Trio, with over 49,000 plays on Spotify, Thrift Store Halo ("TSH"), hails from Chicago, Illinois, and creates polished, modern, hook-heavy, crunchy pop-rock that has a way of getting stuck in your head! NEW EP/mini-LP, "POP-ROCKET" launches 8.15.17 on Hi-Beam Records/Pravda Music. 

Richard Rossi of Power Pop News says: "“I’m Not Through” is first rate guitar pop with it’s shout aloud chorus and memorable melody. It’s easy to like the bouncy “Let’s Not Wait” and “Save Me From Myself” has the catchy chorus and crunchy guitars that place it head and shoulders above the others. While it’s only one of several quite enjoyable songs on Pop Rocket, it’s the standout single for me. Catchy tunes that fit well within the classic power pop template used by bands such as Cheap Trick, Fountains of Wayne and early Tom Petty."

Already in regular rotation on several outlets in the US and UK, TSH's new songs have been featured on Woodyradio ("Secret Weapon") (CAN), KOR Radio (UK), Radio Candy Hits Radio (US), Pop That Goes Crunch (US), The Music Authority (US), SHMU 99.8 FM (Scotland), Belter Radio (UK), 88.7 FM WLUW (Chicago/US). "I'm Not Through" has made Radio Indie Alliance Top 10 in US and UK and Top 40 Overall. "I'm Not Through" also featured on Ice Cream Man Power Pop & More's "Rocking Road" Compilation (released 7.28.17). Podcast showcase on the band debuts on 8.10.17 on Rick's Records Podcast. 

Inspired by a ton of bands such as Cheap Trick, Teenage Fanclub, Fountains of Wayne, Catfish and the Bottlemen, Kings of Leon, The Kooks, Urge Overkill, The Royal Blood, Jet, Boo Radleys, Velvet Crush, Something Happens, The Strokes, Fuzzbuble, Weezer, Jellyfish, Del Amitri, The Struts, and The Jam, and songwriters such as Elvis Costello, Tom Petty and Paul Weller, creating quality, memorable songs is the band's main goal.

html_data:
The Luther Vandross Experience featuring Darron Moore travels worldwide and is a two hour stage production with a live band, costumes, and video production. Celebrate the remarkable legacy of Luther Vandross during this performance of The Luther Vandross Experience featuring Darron Moore. This show brings to life the soul-stirring sounds of Luther Vandross's legendary performances and honors the brilliance and music of one of R&B's most beloved singers.

You’ll relive the unforgettable music and extraordinary dance moves of the legendary Luther Vandross, recreated through a mesmerizing fusion of dancing, eye-catching costumes, and song.

The Luther Vandross Experience encapsulates the multi-faceted artistic output and creative soul of this incredible R&B Artist, a man whose legacy continues to inspire millions to this day.

Enjoy an amazing performance of Luther Vandross’s most beloved hits such as, Never Too Much, Here And Now, Superstar, Stop To Love, Wait For Love, So Amazing, Glow Of Love and many more! By the end of your voyage, you will know it’s the perfect way to honor the musical and cultural legacy of this iconic R&B star, Luther Vandross.

Luther Vandross was an eight time Grammy Award winner and is still an inspiration to countless performers. Darron Moore gives a dynamic and inspiring performance to honor Luther Vandross.

As The Premier Luther Vandross Tribute Band in the nation, The Luther Vandross Experience featuring Darron Moore is a great fit for all Casino, Corporate, Festival, Nightclub, Birthday, Retirement, and Private events. Be it the full 12 piece orchestra or smaller instrument choice, or tracks, The Luther Vandross Experience has the right formula to fit your entertainment budget.

Bring Class and Elegance to your event. Book The Luther Vandross Experience featuring Darron Moore.

Darron is supported by his stage team Tykielah Davis, Unique Cooper, and Dennis McDonald. In addition to the stage performers, Darron's Band members are Music Director and on Drums David Brandon, Percussions Marlone Bee Bop Crawford, Guitar Clarence Williams, Keyboards Antwon Green, and second Keyboards Craig Erqhuart Sr.

Darron Moore and The 14th Floor is a band that offers you a choice of packages based on your budget needs.

Below is a sample of what is available.

This Band Also Performs Motown, Classic Soul, R&B, and cover Various other artists such as Bruno Mars, Beyonce, Sade, and an array of others.

Option 1 Full Band (Recommended)
4 Vocalists 12 Piece Band (2 Keyboards,Drummer,Bass,Guitar,Vibes,Percussions, 4 Piece Horn section,& Harp).

4 Vocalists 7 Piece Band (2 Keyboards,Drummer,Bass,Guitar,2 Piece Horn Section)

Option 3 Track Show
4 Vocalists Live Tracks DJ

Darron Moore and The 14th Floor Discography include,
‘Love’s Flight’, ‘Love’s Flight Reflections’, ‘Darron Moore and The 14th Floor Live!’, and ‘A Real Christmas’.

Temptation, Luther Vandross, Miles Davis, The Spinners, Peabo Bryson, The Ojays, The Dells, The Stylistics, Lamont Dozier, Smokey Robinson,

html_data: Blue Nitro is a dynamic Chicago-based funky blues rock band. Built on a foundation of a high energy rhythm section with soaring vocals and searing guitar on top, Blue Nitro brings the "rock" to blues rock. The band was formed after founder and guitarist Dean Sarantos, a veteran of 20 plus years in Midwestern rock and blues bands, nearly crashed his car listening to some funky, heavy blues tracks while daydreaming about putting together such a group. Soon after the near-crash, Dean recruited Cheryl O. (vocals), Chris Hopper (bass) and John Marrella (drums) to form the band. John's resume includes seven years as the drummer with Rock and Roll Hall of Fame band The Lovin' Spoonful and two years drumming with noted hard rock band Head East. Today, Blue Nitro is entertaining audiences and gaining fans with its scintillating blues rock show and top notch musicianship.

about

 

Lady Patice, The Motown Reflections and the Fantasy Band performs in and around Chicago and nationally as a top Show Band, Motown Band, R & B Band, Blues Band, Funk Band, Jazz Band, Soul Band and Wedding Band. As one of the best dance bands in Chicago the Fantasy Band has performed in concert with some of the most notable entertainers including blues legends BB King, Buddy Guy and Bobby "Blue" Bland. Lady Patice, a Chicago and nationally known show artist, has performed in numerous concerts and festivals nationwide. 

Lady Patice is a Chicago native who was inspired to sing at an early age. She sings R& B, Blues and Gospel. She is currently recording her first CD in the studio on her debut blues album and first single “Mojo Lady”. Her single will be released by the fall of 2016. 

Lady Patice, featuring Monique Houston and The Fantasy Band performs in and around Chicagoland, and nationally. Lady Patice, has performed in numerous concerts and festivals nationwide. 

As one of the leading female vocalist in Chicago, Lady Patice has performed in concert with some of America's most notable recording artist, including blues legends BB King, Buddy Guy, Bobby “Blue” Bland, The Funk Brothers of Motown, Greg Hill's Delfonics, The Chi-Lites, Willie Clayton, Bobby Rush, Otis Clay, TL Williams, and many others. 


Monique Houston, is a local recording artist, and a multi-genre singer who offers a blend of jazz, pop, R&B and soul. Monique has the honor of performing for numerous concerts and festivals nationwide. She has been chosen to perform a tribute to Natalie Cole at the Chicago Music Awards and will be competing for Chicago's Top female emerging artist. 

Born Monique Shirell Houston on June 7th in Chicago Illinois, Monique grew up in a musically inclined family with aunts, uncles and cousins who played various instruments and had great vocal ranges. Her love for music started at the age of 2. Monique has been performing for live audiences since the age 5. Since then she has been sharpening her skills as a vocalist and performer, both on-stage and off. Her strong lead vocals, friendly demeanor, alluring sex appeal, and electrifying stage presence have captivated audiences everywhere. She's performed for audiences in Chicago, Atlanta and many other cities. 

She is truly a natural talent, born to perform with a determination to succeed. 

The Fantasy Band consist of six vary talented male and female musicians. They have recorded and performed for numerous recording artist. The core group consist of lead guitar, bass guitar, two pianist, drummer and a trumpet player.

html_data: DIAMONDBACK: You may know us simply as “the band from Carol’s”. Since 1999, Mike McKeehan (vocals & bass guitar) and Reva Goodman (vocals & rhythm guitar) fronted the house band at everyone’s favorite, award winning, late night honkytonk/dive bar, Carol’s Pub, on Chicago’s Northside. Sadly, that bar is gone, but Diamondback continues to play on. Long time members Lee Borek (lead guitar & vocals) and Jamie Gallagher (drums and vocals) are now joined by multi-instrumentalist and singer, Pat Kiener. We still serve up our patented mix of classic country, Americana and new country that’s guaranteed to have folks singing along and partying from the first song. Our extensive song list promises something for everyone. Diamondback remains committed to bringing Classic Honky Tonk music to the urban masses! It’s going to be a down home good time! Diamondback also performs as a trio (DB3) for smaller venues. Thanks for your consideration!!
short_desc: Classic Country and so much more!

html_data: Animal Farm is a Chicago-based group of musicians and educators who write original music for kids and families (also known as "kindie-rock"). Our songs explore themes of self-expression and communities through the eyes of animals. Blending a variety of musical styles including, but not limited to rock n' roll, vaudeville, tango, and afro-pop, we offer listeners an eclectic sound and an energetic stage show. We've been appropriately dubbed, "Grownup Music for Kids." We have over three hours of material and can tailor our performance to your specific needs. Because of the breadth of our appeal, we play a large variety of venues from backyards to festivals and every size in between. We are an ideal fit for any daytime festival performance as we have a large following of families who will come out for earlier performances. Our upbeat and energetic shows have been a hit at community festivals and events throughout Chicagoland, including Prairie Fest (Oswego), the Morton Arboretum, Taste of River North, Breakfast with Santa (Alsip Park District), the Field Museum, the Garfield Park Conservatory, as well as dozens of shows at schools, libraries, and parks.
short_desc: Animal Farm is a Chicago-based group of musicians and educators who write original music for kids and families (also known as "kindie-rock").

name: The Beat Bank (Brother El, The Present Elders and Makers of Sense)
html_data:
The Beat Bank is an independent record label featuring various styles of avant-garde electronic music; working mainly in fusion styles. They value true artist development, creative content and quality productions as opposed to quantity and trend.

It was founded in 1995 by Lional [Brother El] Freeman as merely a music production and recording studio. As the success of The Beat Banks projects grew and the talent pool developed, Brother El partnered with his then manager Charles Cain and expanded the company into a full service record label.  This was mainly due to their growing catalogue of unreleased music and lack of proper business representation in Chicago Hip Hop music.

Currently, the label is partnering with major electronic distributors to launch its newest acts and becoming leading advocate for “Live PA” electronic music performance.  The Beat Bank’s collaborations include hip hop collective Bare Witness (consisting of Chicago Hip Hop legends), electronic experimental act “Makers Of Sense” and most recently “The Present Elders” who recently came to prominence due to a series of pop up shows held at culturally significant areas of Chicago.  Furthermore, Brother El has worked with multiple Chicago institutions including The University of Chicago, Old Town School of Folk Music, The Department of Cultural Affairs, The Oakland Museum of Contemporary Art, Knobcon, and Loyola University.

html_data: Industrial Drive is a cover band that plays an extremely eclectic variety of popular rock music from the late 1970s through current hits. In addition to excellent musicianship, including possibly the best lead guitarist in Chicago, Industrial Drive does a lot of favorite songs that you just don’t hear a lot of cover bands play – songs like December by Collective Soul, Sister Golden Hair by America, Walk by the Foo Fighters, If You Could Only See by Tonic, Love Song by The Cure, and Mysterious Ways by U2. They also do standard favorites like Brown Eyed Girl by Van Morrison, Your Love by the Outfield, Summer of ’69 by Bryan Adams, Sweet Child O’ Mine by Guns and Roses, and Hard To Handle by Black Crows. Industrial Drive will work within your budget; and, you won’t find a more professional and easy to work with group of guys. Industrial Drive gets booked year after year at venues like MT Barrels in Schaumburg, Joe’s Live in Rosemont, the Buffalo Grove Days festival, and many summer concerts in the park. And, they have opened for popular bands like 7th Heaven, LAVA Rock, Rock of Ages, and Kashmir. Visit their website at industrialdrive.net; you will absolutely love this band!
short_desc: Industrial Drive is a cover band that plays an extremely eclectic variety of popular rock music from the late 1970s through current hits.

html_data: Matt Muse is a Hip-Hop artist/producer from Chicago. With a bold presence, dynamic lyricism, & a one of a kind live performance, Matt Muse has become a mainstay in the Chicago Hip-Hop scene while quietly, but certainly, moving toward national recognition. He was featured on ‘Sway in the Morning’ in the summer of 2015, and he has performed at multiple venues throughout Chicago; the most notable being headlining Chicago’s TIP Fest in July 2016 & on the September 2016 ‘AAHH! Fest’ main stage alongside J. Cole, Common, Vic Mensa, The Roots & more. Matt was a featured speaker at the 2016 NIU TEDx event where he did a TED Talk that discussed the impact that Hip-Hop has had on his life & many others. In March 2017, he released his debut EP The SiKK Tape via Midwest hip-hop blog Fake Shore Drive. It has since been featured in & praised by The Chicago Reader, France based music blog Da Water, as well as numerous other blogs and publications. On March 29, 2017, Muse embarked on a 13-stop promotional tour for The SiKK Tape that spanned the Eastern and Southern parts of the United States, as well as a stop in Canada. The tour featured three shows (Cincinnati, OH, Cleveland, OH, & Bloomington, IN) where Matt performed as support on Malcolm London’s Opia Tour. Matt’s first ever tour commenced on June 28 in Toronto and served as a flawless start to a new chapter of Matt’s career and a solid boost to his listeners outside of the Midwest. Currently, Matt is recording his debut album set to release in Spring 2018, and preparing for his headlining performance at the 2018 Taste of Chicago.
short_desc: Matt Muse is a Hip-Hop artist/producer from Chicago

html_data: Stampy is a mainly original project based out of Chicago, IL. Stampy is available for events ranging from festivals to weddings to private parties to intimate soundstage appearances. OFFICIAL BIO Elephants are a dynamic animal, both intelligent and gentle, but when riled up can be thunderous and powerful. The same has been said of Stampy and their unique sound. The Chicago-based quintet fuses together soulful grooves, dense vocal harmonies, and high energy guitar solos that roar through venues. Five long-time friends have come together to create a sound ‘where Steely Dan meets The Allman Brothers meets Wilco…. with a dab of Pet Sounds.’ Each time Stampy comes to the stage, it is “eclectic. Stampy’s original music appears to derive influences from across the musical spectrum.” Five seasoned singers and songwriters, all hailing from different musical backgrounds, have forged a sound that is truly unique and appealing to all fans of music. From the start, Stampy attracted fans in droves from all areas and genres of Chicago’s live music community. In just two months, the cost of their first album was funded entirely thanks to the contributions from their loyal fanbase. Like a stampede, the band came running full speed out of the gate. Within months of inception the group was in the studio cutting their debut album and playing at some of Chicago’s most prestigious and historic venues. After self-producing their first album, the band brought in legendary sound guru, Fred Breitberg (Aretha Franklin, Neil Young, Curtis Mayfield), to mix and master it. Fred’s expertise put the finishing touches on a record that is making a statement. Stampy finished out 2017 with a show alongside guitar virtuoso Fareed Haque. Martyrs in Chicago, IL. The quintet has also begun work on their second album, 'Expectations' (2018). You will be able to hear each member being featured as a lead singer and primary songwriter on at least one song, showcasing the band’s immense creativity and vast musical perspective. Because of this, they have dug deeper on their new album. Songs are crafted in a thematic way. Subjects such as friendship, love, greed, inspiration, and faith will be represented. Keep posted for news surrounding the future release of Stampy's second album. Come witness the thunderous and powerful sound for yourself. The band’s live show was translated brilliantly to their debut record and will surely be continued on their second release. But to fully experience the dynamic range, the roaring guitar solos, intricate songwriting, and beautiful vocal harmonies, you must see Stampy perform live. They just might become your new favorite artist. EPK: https://www.stampymusic.com/epk
short_desc: Stampy is a mainly original project based out of Chicago, IL

html_data:
Jalen Romell is a singer songwriter from Milwaukee, Wisconsin and poster boi for Urban Folk and anti opioids. This young musician known around Milwaukee’s budding music scene continues to amaze fans and create dimensions and layers to his artistry known as Urban-folk. After a good debut album entitled “Believe It” Jalen has added depth to his sound. Jalen’s freshman album “Believe It” was a soulful, gentle, edgy and refreshing album as it went against current trends of folk and r&b. Songs of love, heartbreak, separation, acceptance and passion filled this album which is still opening a few eyes to Jalen’s uncanny talents. Jalen’s debuted video from “Believe it” was “That Feeling”, directed by Emmy Award winning film producer Brendon Carter ( ex. Gene Simmons Family Tree). “That feeling” carried an anti opioid message and support for loved ones struggling with dependency from pills, while the albums title track “Believe it” addresses social unity and rebuilding. Jalen has remained dedicated to social change, love and unity. He continues to writing meaningful lyrics and develop this universal sound that reaches fans of folk, R & b, hip hop and pop. Urban-folk, guitar leading a rhythmic composition of hip hop kicks and snares, percussion or maybe an occasional trap roll. The combination of these unlikely ingredients makes for a great canvas for Jalen Romell’s soulful vocals and substance.
 
Jalen has won over fans with performances at events and festivals such as Brady Fest (Dry Hooch), Milwaukee’s Washington Park Band shell with Charles Walker Band, Chicago’s Uncommon Ground near Legendary Wrigley’s Field and Soulful Sunday’s at Milwaukee’s Art Museum under the Brise Soleil. Open yourself up to this uncommon blend of folk music, soul, urban and rhythm that is undeniably good to listen too.
 
Jalen’s sophomore album “White Walls” Ep, is a self written, co produced album that delivers more of that Acoustic flavor with a kick of that youthful vibe that’s extremely popular with this

html_data: We are a 3-piece pop rock band from Chicago. Our live show is fun, fast, and we get the crowd dancing. We are a great festival band because our music is pop, upbeat, and our sound appeals to a broad audience. Please view our full EPK at http://loveinoctober.com/epk The band formed in Minneapolis, MN in 2007 and has rotated band members over the years with the Widman brothers as the common denominator. The group has released six albums, toured the US and Canada, and been featured in national magazines such as Spin and Paste. The band is working on their seventh album to be released in 2018.
